bsnWireless.description: This MIB is intended to be implemented on all those devices operating as Central Controllers (CC) that terminate the Light Weight Access Point Protocol tunnel from Light-weight LWAPP Access Points. This MIB provides configuration and status information for 802.11 Access Points, LAN configuration, AAA, Mobility, IpSec, Radio Rescouce Management and 802.11 global parameters. The relationship between controller and the LWAPP APs can be depicted as follows: +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + CC + + CC + + CC + + CC + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ .. . . . .. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + + + AP + + AP + + AP + + AP + + AP + + + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + + + MN + + MN + + MN + + MN + + MN + + + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ The LWAPP tunnel exists between the controller and the APs. The MNs communicate with the APs through the protocol defined by the 802.11 standard. LWAPP APs, upon bootup, discover and join one of the controllers and the controller pushes the configuration, that includes the WLAN parameters, to the LWAPP APs. The APs then encapsulate all the 802.11 frames from wireless clients inside LWAPP frames and forward the LWAPP frames to the controller. GLOSSARY Access Point ( AP ) An entity that contains an 802.11 medium access control ( MAC ) and physical layer ( PHY ) interface and provides access to the distribution services via the wireless medium for associated clients. LWAPP APs encapsulate all the 802.11 frames in LWAPP frames and sends it to the controller to which it is logically connected. Basic Service Set Identifier (BSSID) The identifier for the service set comprising of all the 802.11 stations under the control of one coordinating Access Point. This identifier happens to be the MAC address of the dot11 radio interface of the Access Point. The wireless clients that associate with the Access Point get the wired uplink through this particular dot11 interface. Central Controller ( CC ) The central entity that terminates the LWAPP protocol tunnel from the LWAPP APs. Throughout this MIB, this entity also referred to as 'controller'. Light Weight Access Point Protocol ( LWAPP ) This is a generic protocol that defines the communication between the Access Points and the Central Controller. Mobile Node ( MN ) A roaming 802.11 wireless device in a wireless network associated with an access point. Station Management (SMT) This term refers to the internal management of the 802.11 protocol operations by the AP to work cooperatively with the other APs and 802.11 devices in the network. REFERENCE [1] Part 11 Wireless LAN Medium Access Control ( MAC ) and Physical Layer ( PHY ) Specifications. [2] Draft-obara-capwap-lwapp-00.txt, IETF Light Weight Access Point Protocol.

BsnTxtSignatureMacInfo.name: BsnTxtSignatureMacInfo
BsnTxtSignatureMacInfo.description: This textual convention defines the pattern followed by the LWAPP APs to perform signature analysis with the signature and report the results to the Controller. The semantics are described as follows. bsnSignatureMacAll - The Controller would set the 'Mac Info' parameter of the 'Signature Add LWAPP Message' to this value to indicate the LWAPP AP that the signature analysis and pattern matching should be tracked and reported on a per-signature and per-channel basis. bsnSignatureMacIndividual - The Controller would set the 'Mac Info' parameter of the 'Signature Add LWAPP Message' to this value to indicate the LWAPP AP that the signature analysis and pattern matching should be tracked and reported separately for individual MAC addresses, that are the sources of the received 802.11 data and/or management frames. bsnStandardSigMacBoth - The Controller would set the 'Mac Info' parameter of the 'Signature Add LWAPP Message' to this value to indicate the LWAPP AP that the signature analysis and pattern matching should be tracked on a per signature as well as per-MAC address basis.

BsnSignaturePatternOffSetStart.name: BsnSignaturePatternOffSetStart
BsnSignaturePatternOffSetStart.description: This object indicates how an offset should be applied while doing signature analysis for QOS and non-QOS data frames. This is introduced since 802.11e QOS frames have an additional 2-byte QOS header which results in the current implementation not being able to find the start of the date frames for signature analysis. The semantics of the values are as follows. sigPattStartFrm - This indicates that the required offset should be applied to the start of the data frame, before performing pattern matching of the signature on the data frame. sigPattStartFrmBody - This value indicates that the required offset should be applied to the start of the frame body, after the header, before performing pattern matching of the signature on the data frame.

bsnDot11EssTable.name: bsnDot11EssTable
bsnDot11EssTable.description: Ess(WLAN) Configuration Table indexed by bsnDot11EssIndex. Maximum of 17 WLANs can be created on Airespace Switch. bsnDot11EssIndex of 17 is reserved for WLAN for Third Party APs(non-Airespace APs).

bsnDot11EssIndex.name: bsnDot11EssIndex
bsnDot11EssIndex.description: Index of the Ess(WLAN) within Airespace Switch. Airespace Switch supports 517 ESS(Wlans) so index will be from 1 to 517. 517 is to be used for ESS(WLAN) created for support of Third Party APs(non-Airespace APs)

bsnDot11EssSessionTimeout.name: bsnDot11EssSessionTimeout
bsnDot11EssSessionTimeout.description: Maximum time of a Mobile Station session. Value of 0 means infinite time(no timeout set).

bsnDot11EssMacFiltering.name: bsnDot11EssMacFiltering
bsnDot11EssMacFiltering.description: A type of security policy for Mobile Stations (Clients). Select to filter clients by MAC address. By selecting this Security, you need to create MacFilters in bsnUsersTable or have MacFilters configured on Radius Servers specified in bsnRadiusAuthenticationTable

bsnDot11EssAdminStatus.name: bsnDot11EssAdminStatus
bsnDot11EssAdminStatus.description: Administrative Status of ESS(WLAN). By disabling an ESS the corresponding SSID is no longer broadcasted in AP beacons.

bsnDot11EssStaticWEPSecurity.name: bsnDot11EssStaticWEPSecurity
bsnDot11EssStaticWEPSecurity.description: Status of Static WEP Security policy. If enabled, WEP Encryption WEP Default Key, Key Index and Key Format should also be specified.

bsnDot11EssStaticWEPEncryptionType.name: bsnDot11EssStaticWEPEncryptionType
bsnDot11EssStaticWEPEncryptionType.description: Type of Static WEP Encryption. Length of key specified in Default Key depends on this attribute.

bsnDot11EssStaticWEPDefaultKey.name: bsnDot11EssStaticWEPDefaultKey
bsnDot11EssStaticWEPDefaultKey.description: Static WEP Default Key. For wep104 encryption either 26 bit hex key or 13 bit ascii key should be specified. For wep40 encryption 10 bit hex key or 5 bit ascii key should be specified. For wep128 encryption 32 bit hex key or 16 bit ascii key should be specified.

bsnDot11EssStaticWEPKeyIndex.name: bsnDot11EssStaticWEPKeyIndex
bsnDot11EssStaticWEPKeyIndex.description: According to 802.11 standard 4 keys are supported. So 802.11 Mobile Stations(Client) can have upto 4 keys. This index is for informing Mobile Station which key it should use for Static WEP Authentication

bsnDot11EssStaticWEPKeyFormat.name: bsnDot11EssStaticWEPKeyFormat
bsnDot11EssStaticWEPKeyFormat.description: This is not persistant.Reading this attribute will always return default. The format of the key specified in Airespace switch keeps record of the Index.

bsnDot11Ess8021xEncryptionType.name: bsnDot11Ess8021xEncryptionType
bsnDot11Ess8021xEncryptionType.description: Type of 802.1X Encryption. This applies if bsnDot11Ess8021xSecurity is in enabled state.

bsnDot11EssWPASecurity.name: bsnDot11EssWPASecurity
bsnDot11EssWPASecurity.description: Status of WPA security policy. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssWPAEncryptionType.name: bsnDot11EssWPAEncryptionType
bsnDot11EssWPAEncryptionType.description: Type of WPA Encryption. This applies when bsnDot11EssWPASecurity is in enable state. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssIpsecSecurity.name: bsnDot11EssIpsecSecurity
bsnDot11EssIpsecSecurity.description: Status of IpSec (VPN) security policy. Note that this cannot be applied with Web security policy.

bsnDot11EssVpnEncrTransform.name: bsnDot11EssVpnEncrTransform
bsnDot11EssVpnEncrTransform.description: The Encryption algorithm employed by this Vpn(IpSec) Encryption. This applies only when bsnDot11EssIpsecSecurity is in enable state.

bsnDot11EssVpnAuthTransform.name: bsnDot11EssVpnAuthTransform
bsnDot11EssVpnAuthTransform.description: The Hash algorithm employed by the Vpn Encrpytion. This applies only when bsnDot11EssIpsecSecurity is in enable state.

bsnDot11EssVpnIkeAuthMode.name: bsnDot11EssVpnIkeAuthMode
bsnDot11EssVpnIkeAuthMode.description: The authentication type of the SA. It could be a certificate or a pre-shared key or xauthEnablePsk. This applies only when bsnDot11EssIpsecSecurity is in enable state.

bsnDot11EssVpnSharedKey.name: bsnDot11EssVpnSharedKey
bsnDot11EssVpnSharedKey.description: VPN Shared Key. This applies only when bsnDot11EssVpnSharedKey is in enable state and bsnDot11EssVpnIkeAuthMode is xauthEnablePsk or presharedKey.

bsnDot11EssVpnSharedKeySize.name: bsnDot11EssVpnSharedKeySize
bsnDot11EssVpnSharedKeySize.description: VPN Shared Key size. This applies only when bsnDot11EssVpnSharedKey is in enable state and bsnDot11EssVpnIkeAuthMode is xauthEnablePsk or presharedKey.

bsnDot11EssVpnIkePhase1Mode.name: bsnDot11EssVpnIkePhase1Mode
bsnDot11EssVpnIkePhase1Mode.description: VPN IKE Phase 1 Mode type as per the IpSec standards. This applies only when bsnDot11EssIpsecSecurity is in enable state.

bsnDot11EssVpnIkeLifetime.name: bsnDot11EssVpnIkeLifetime
bsnDot11EssVpnIkeLifetime.description: Vpn IKE's Lifetime. This applies only when bsnDot11EssIpsecSecurity is in enable state.

bsnDot11EssVpnIkeDHGroup.name: bsnDot11EssVpnIkeDHGroup
bsnDot11EssVpnIkeDHGroup.description: IKE's Diffie-Hellman Group. This applies only when bsnDot11EssIpsecSecurity is in enable state.

bsnDot11EssIpsecPassthruSecurity.name: bsnDot11EssIpsecPassthruSecurity
bsnDot11EssIpsecPassthruSecurity.description: Status of IpSec Passthru security policy.

bsnDot11EssVpnPassthruGateway.name: bsnDot11EssVpnPassthruGateway
bsnDot11EssVpnPassthruGateway.description: Ip address of VpnPassthru Gateway. This applies only when bsnDot11EssIpsecPassthruSecurity is in enable state.

bsnDot11EssWebSecurity.name: bsnDot11EssWebSecurity
bsnDot11EssWebSecurity.description: Status of Web security policy. Note this policy cannot be applied with IpSec security policy.

bsnDot11EssRadioPolicy.name: bsnDot11EssRadioPolicy
bsnDot11EssRadioPolicy.description: Radio Policy for a WLAN. It can either be All where it will be applicable to ALL types of protocols or it can be set to apply to combinations of 802.11a, 802.11b, 802.11g.

bsnDot11EssQualityOfService.name: bsnDot11EssQualityOfService
bsnDot11EssQualityOfService.description: Quality of Service for a WLAN.Services such as VoIP should be set to Gold while non-discriminating services such as messaging can be set to Bronze.

bsnDot11EssDhcpRequired.name: bsnDot11EssDhcpRequired
bsnDot11EssDhcpRequired.description: DHCP required for all clients on this WLAN

bsnDot11EssDhcpServerIpAddress.name: bsnDot11EssDhcpServerIpAddress
bsnDot11EssDhcpServerIpAddress.description: IP Address of the DHCP Server. Make it 0.0.0.0 to disable DHCP Relay. Any value other than 0.0.0.0, it will be assumed that DHCP Relay is turned on.

bsnDot11EssVpnContivityMode.name: bsnDot11EssVpnContivityMode
bsnDot11EssVpnContivityMode.description: Specifies if contivity mode for the IpSec is enabled. If enabled, user needs to specify the Quote of the Day Server's IPAddress in bsnDot11EssVpnQotdServerAddress.

bsnDot11EssVpnQotdServerAddress.name: bsnDot11EssVpnQotdServerAddress
bsnDot11EssVpnQotdServerAddress.description: IP Address of the Quote of the Day Server.

bsnDot11EssBlacklistTimeout.name: bsnDot11EssBlacklistTimeout
bsnDot11EssBlacklistTimeout.description: Set the timeout for blacklisted Mobile Stations after which the mobile station will be automatically de-authenticated. Mobile Station are blacklisted by MAC address and their status can be obtained from bsnMobileStationStatus. A timeout setting of 0 indicates no blacklist timeout is set and administrative control (bsnMobileStationDeleteAction ) is required to deauthenticate the station.

bsnDot11EssNumberOfMobileStations.name: bsnDot11EssNumberOfMobileStations
bsnDot11EssNumberOfMobileStations.description: No of Mobile Stations currently associated with the WLAN.

bsnDot11EssWebPassthru.name: bsnDot11EssWebPassthru
bsnDot11EssWebPassthru.description: For switches with version before 2.0: This is applicable only when the Web Security Type is enabled. When this attribute is enabled, it allows a client's NetBIOS packets to go through the switch before web auth is completed. (This is obsolete for Switch versions 2.0 to 2.2). For switch verions 3.0 and above: This is reintroduced as the web policy where the client is connected through the web without authentication that is there is no username/password input required. Moreover, if the bsnDot11EssWebPassthroughEmail is enabled, the user will be asked to enter an email address.

bsnDot11EssCraniteSecurity.name: bsnDot11EssCraniteSecurity
bsnDot11EssCraniteSecurity.description: Status of Cranite Passthrough Security policy. If enabled, no other security can be enabled.

bsnDot11EssBlacklistingCapability.name: bsnDot11EssBlacklistingCapability
bsnDot11EssBlacklistingCapability.description: This is the flag that can enable or disable the client backlisting feature for a WLAN. If enabled, the clients can be blacklisted by the Switch in case of repetitive auth failure and other reasons like it. If disabled, the clients cannot be blacklisted by the switch. The blacklist timeout value will only be effective if this feature is turned on.

bsnDot11EssInterfaceName.name: bsnDot11EssInterfaceName
bsnDot11EssInterfaceName.description: Name of the interface used by this WLAN. By default it is set to be the management interface.

bsnDot11EssAclName.name: bsnDot11EssAclName
bsnDot11EssAclName.description: Name of ACL for the WLAN. This is applicable only when Web Authentication is enabled as a security. An empty string value indicates that no ACL has been set (which is a valid option)

bsnDot11EssAAAOverride.name: bsnDot11EssAAAOverride
bsnDot11EssAAAOverride.description: Enable or Disable AAA override for the global WLAN parameters.

bsnDot11EssWPAAuthKeyMgmtMode.name: bsnDot11EssWPAAuthKeyMgmtMode
bsnDot11EssWPAAuthKeyMgmtMode.description: Enable or Disable WPA Pre-shared Key Mode. If enabled, a preshared key should be set for WPA authentication. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssWPAAuthPresharedKey.name: bsnDot11EssWPAAuthPresharedKey
bsnDot11EssWPAAuthPresharedKey.description: WPA Authentication Preshared Key. This applies only when bsnDot11EssWPAAuthKeyMgmtMode is in enable state. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssWepAllowSharedKeyAuth.name: bsnDot11EssWepAllowSharedKeyAuth
bsnDot11EssWepAllowSharedKeyAuth.description: Enable this flag to allow Shared Key Authentication when Static WEP is enabled.

bsnDot11EssFortressSecurity.name: bsnDot11EssFortressSecurity
bsnDot11EssFortressSecurity.description: Status of Fortress Passthrough Security policy. If enabled, no other security can be enabled.

bsnDot11EssL2tpSecurity.name: bsnDot11EssL2tpSecurity
bsnDot11EssL2tpSecurity.description: Status of L2TP security policy. Note that this cannot be applied with Web security policy, Cranite or Fortress policy.

bsnDot11EssWPAAuthPresharedKeyHex.name: bsnDot11EssWPAAuthPresharedKeyHex
bsnDot11EssWPAAuthPresharedKeyHex.description: WPA Authentication Preshared Key in the hex format. This applies only when bsnDot11EssWPAAuthKeyMgmtMode is in enable state. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssBroadcastSsid.name: bsnDot11EssBroadcastSsid
bsnDot11EssBroadcastSsid.description: This attribute when enabled allows the switch to broadcast this SSID.

bsnDot11EssExternalPolicyValidation.name: bsnDot11EssExternalPolicyValidation
bsnDot11EssExternalPolicyValidation.description: This attribute specifies if external policy servers will be used for validation. If no servers are configured in bsnExternalPolicyServerTable then it cannot be enabled.

bsnDot11EssRSNSecurity.name: bsnDot11EssRSNSecurity
bsnDot11EssRSNSecurity.description: This attribute specifies status of RSN Security Policy. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssRSNWPACompatibilityMode.name: bsnDot11EssRSNWPACompatibilityMode
bsnDot11EssRSNWPACompatibilityMode.description: This attribute specifies RSN security's compatibility mode with WPA. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssRSNAllowTKIPClients.name: bsnDot11EssRSNAllowTKIPClients
bsnDot11EssRSNAllowTKIPClients.description: This attribute specifies whether TKIP clients are allowed by RSN Policy. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssRSNAuthKeyMgmtMode.name: bsnDot11EssRSNAuthKeyMgmtMode
bsnDot11EssRSNAuthKeyMgmtMode.description: This attribute specifies whether Preshared key is used or not. If used user should specify a key between 8 and 63 characters in bsnDot11EssRSNAuthPresharedKey attribute. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssRSNAuthPresharedKey.name: bsnDot11EssRSNAuthPresharedKey
bsnDot11EssRSNAuthPresharedKey.description: RSN Authentication Preshared Key. This applies only when bsnDot11EssRSNAuthKeyMgmtMode is in enable state. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssRSNAuthPresharedKeyHex.name: bsnDot11EssRSNAuthPresharedKeyHex
bsnDot11EssRSNAuthPresharedKeyHex.description: RSN Authentication Preshared Key in the hex format. This applies only when bsnDot11EssWPAAuthKeyMgmtMode is in enable state. This has been deprecated for cLWSecDot11EssCckmTable.

bsnDot11EssIPv6Bridging.name: bsnDot11EssIPv6Bridging
bsnDot11EssIPv6Bridging.description: When enabled, IPv6 bridging is applied on the packets.

bsnDot11EssRowStatus.name: bsnDot11EssRowStatus
bsnDot11EssRowStatus.description: A row status type for the bsnDot11EssEntry

bsnDot11EssWmePolicySetting.name: bsnDot11EssWmePolicySetting
bsnDot11EssWmePolicySetting.description: When enabled, WME Policy is applied on the packets.

bsnDot11Ess80211ePolicySetting.name: bsnDot11Ess80211ePolicySetting
bsnDot11Ess80211ePolicySetting.description: When enabled, 802.11e Policy is applied on the packets.

bsnDot11EssWebPassthroughEmail.name: bsnDot11EssWebPassthroughEmail
bsnDot11EssWebPassthroughEmail.description: When enabled, along with the bsnDot11EssWebPassthru attribute, the client is allowed to connect by entering his/her email address on the web connection page. There is no further authentication required.

bsnDot11Ess7920PhoneSupport.name: bsnDot11Ess7920PhoneSupport
bsnDot11Ess7920PhoneSupport.description: When client cac limit is enabled, the 7920 Phones with old software where the Call Admission Control (CAC) Limit is Specified on the client will be supported on the WLAN. The support for clientCacLimit (by setting to value 1 or 3) cannot be enabled when the bsnDot11EssWmePolicySetting is set to allowed or required. When ap cac limit is enabled, the 7920 Phones with new software where the Call Admission Control (CAC) Limit is advertised by the AP, will be supported on the WLAN.

bsnDot11EssRadiusAuthPrimaryServer.name: bsnDot11EssRadiusAuthPrimaryServer
bsnDot11EssRadiusAuthPrimaryServer.description: Primary Radius Authentication Server for this wlan.

bsnDot11EssRadiusAuthSecondaryServer.name: bsnDot11EssRadiusAuthSecondaryServer
bsnDot11EssRadiusAuthSecondaryServer.description: Secondary Radius Authentication Server for this wlan.

bsnDot11EssRadiusAuthTertiaryServer.name: bsnDot11EssRadiusAuthTertiaryServer
bsnDot11EssRadiusAuthTertiaryServer.description: Tertiary Radius Authentication Server for this wlan.

bsnDot11EssRadiusAcctPrimaryServer.name: bsnDot11EssRadiusAcctPrimaryServer
bsnDot11EssRadiusAcctPrimaryServer.description: Primary Radius Accounting Server for this wlan.

bsnDot11EssRadiusAcctSecondaryServer.name: bsnDot11EssRadiusAcctSecondaryServer
bsnDot11EssRadiusAcctSecondaryServer.description: Secondary Radius Accounting Server for this wlan.

bsnDot11EssRadiusAcctTertiaryServer.name: bsnDot11EssRadiusAcctTertiaryServer
bsnDot11EssRadiusAcctTertiaryServer.description: Tertiary Radius Accounting Server for this wlan.

bsnDot11QosProfileTable.name: bsnDot11QosProfileTable
bsnDot11QosProfileTable.description: QOS Profiles specified in bsnDot11EssTable can be customized in this table. This is a lookup table for auto created profiles

bsnDot11QosProfileName.name: bsnDot11QosProfileName
bsnDot11QosProfileName.description: QOS Profile Name. This will be one of bronze,gold, platinum,silver,uranium.

bsnDot11QosAverageDataRate.name: bsnDot11QosAverageDataRate
bsnDot11QosAverageDataRate.description: This is one of the per user bandwidth contracts(k). Specifies Average Data Rate per user. Value of 0 indicates the feature is disabled.

bsnDot11QosBurstDataRate.name: bsnDot11QosBurstDataRate
bsnDot11QosBurstDataRate.description: This is one of the per user bandwidth contracts(k). Specifies Average Burst Data Rate per user. Value of 0 indicates the feature is disabled.

bsnDot11QosAvgRealTimeDataRate.name: bsnDot11QosAvgRealTimeDataRate
bsnDot11QosAvgRealTimeDataRate.description: This is one of the per user bandwidth contracts(k). Specifies Average Real Time Data Rate per user. Value of 0 indicates the feature is disabled.

bsnDot11QosBurstRealTimeDataRate.name: bsnDot11QosBurstRealTimeDataRate
bsnDot11QosBurstRealTimeDataRate.description: This is one of the per user bandwidth contracts(k). Specifies Burst Real Time Data Rate per user. Value of 0 indicates the feature is disabled.

bsnDot11QosMaxRFUsagePerAP.name: bsnDot11QosMaxRFUsagePerAP
bsnDot11QosMaxRFUsagePerAP.description: This is one of the over the Air QOS parameter. Specifies maximum RF Usage per AP in percentage.

bsnDot11QosProfileQueueDepth.name: bsnDot11QosProfileQueueDepth
bsnDot11QosProfileQueueDepth.description: This is one of the over the Air QOS parameter. Specifies Queue depth for the current profile.

bsnDot11WiredQosProtocol.name: bsnDot11WiredQosProtocol
bsnDot11WiredQosProtocol.description: This is one of the over the Air QOS parameter. Specifies Queue depth for the current profile.

bsnDot11802Dot1PTag.name: bsnDot11802Dot1PTag
bsnDot11802Dot1PTag.description: Specifies the type of wired QOS protocol for the current profile. Value of 0 indicates the feature is disabled.

bsnDot11ResetProfileToDefault.name: bsnDot11ResetProfileToDefault
bsnDot11ResetProfileToDefault.description: Set this attribute to reset to restore the factory default value for the profile.

bsnMobileStationTable.name: bsnMobileStationTable
bsnMobileStationTable.description: Mobile Station Table indexed by bsnMobileStationMacAddress. (Mobile Station is better referred to as Client in the current releases.)

bsnMobileStationMacAddress.name: bsnMobileStationMacAddress
bsnMobileStationMacAddress.description: 802.11 MAC Address of the Mobile Station.

bsnMobileStationIpAddress.name: bsnMobileStationIpAddress
bsnMobileStationIpAddress.description: IP Address of the Mobile Station

bsnMobileStationUserName.name: bsnMobileStationUserName
bsnMobileStationUserName.description: User Name,if any, of the Mobile Station. This would be non empty in case of Web Authentication and IPSec.

bsnMobileStationAPMacAddr.name: bsnMobileStationAPMacAddr
bsnMobileStationAPMacAddr.description: 802.11 Mac Address of the AP to which the Mobile Station is associated.

bsnMobileStationAPIfSlotId.name: bsnMobileStationAPIfSlotId
bsnMobileStationAPIfSlotId.description: Slot ID of AP Interface to which the mobile station is associated. The value 15 is used to indicate that the slot Id is invalid.

bsnMobileStationEssIndex.name: bsnMobileStationEssIndex
bsnMobileStationEssIndex.description: Ess Index of the Wlan(SSID) that is being used by Mobile Station to connect to AP

bsnMobileStationSsid.name: bsnMobileStationSsid
bsnMobileStationSsid.description: The SSID Advertised by Mobile Station

bsnMobileStationReasonCode.name: bsnMobileStationReasonCode
bsnMobileStationReasonCode.description: Reason Code as defined by 802.11 standards

bsnMobileStationMobilityStatus.name: bsnMobileStationMobilityStatus
bsnMobileStationMobilityStatus.description: Mobility Role of the Mobile Station.

bsnMobileStationAnchorAddress.name: bsnMobileStationAnchorAddress
bsnMobileStationAnchorAddress.description: If the Mobility Status of the Mobile Station is Anchor then it will have Peer Ip Address and will have Anchor IP if the Role is Foreign

bsnMobileStationCFPollable.name: bsnMobileStationCFPollable
bsnMobileStationCFPollable.description: When this attribute is true, it shall indicate that the Mobile Station is able to respond to a CF-Poll with a data frame within a SIFS time. This attribute shall be false if the Mobile Station is not able to respond to a CF-Poll with a data frame within a SIFS time.

bsnMobileStationCFPollRequest.name: bsnMobileStationCFPollRequest
bsnMobileStationCFPollRequest.description: Specifies whether CFP is requested by Mobile Station or not

bsnMobileStationChannelAgilityEnabled.name: bsnMobileStationChannelAgilityEnabled
bsnMobileStationChannelAgilityEnabled.description: This attribute indicates that the PHY channel agility functionality is enabled.

bsnMobileStationPBCCOptionImplemented.name: bsnMobileStationPBCCOptionImplemented
bsnMobileStationPBCCOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the PBCC modulation option as defined in subclause 18.4.6.6 is implemented. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

bsnMobileStationShortPreambleOptionImple.name: bsnMobileStationShortPreambleOptionImplemented
bsnMobileStationShortPreambleOptionImple.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the short preamble option as defined in subclause 18.2.2.2 is implemented. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

bsnMobileStationPortNumber.name: bsnMobileStationPortNumber
bsnMobileStationPortNumber.description: The Port Number of this Airespace Switch on which the traffic of the Mobile Station is coming through.

bsnMobileStationDeleteAction.name: bsnMobileStationDeleteAction
bsnMobileStationDeleteAction.description: Action to Deauthenticate the Mobile Station. Set the State to delete.

bsnMobileStationPolicyManagerState.name: bsnMobileStationPolicyManagerState
bsnMobileStationPolicyManagerState.description: Policy Manager State of the mobile station.

bsnMobileStationSecurityPolicyStatus.name: bsnMobileStationSecurityPolicyStatus
bsnMobileStationSecurityPolicyStatus.description: When this attribute has value completed, it shall indicate that the Mobile Station has completed the security policy checks. Otherwise the checks are yet to be completed.

bsnMobileStationProtocol.name: bsnMobileStationProtocol
bsnMobileStationProtocol.description: The 802.11 protocol type of the client. The protocol is mobile when this client detail is seen on the anchor i.e it's mobility status is anchor.

bsnMobileStationMirrorMode.name: bsnMobileStationMirrorMode
bsnMobileStationMirrorMode.description: If enabled, then mirroring for this client will be statically configured irrespective of the AP and the port this client is on.

bsnMobileStationInterface.name: bsnMobileStationInterface
bsnMobileStationInterface.description: Name of the Interface of the mobile client to the switch.

bsnMobileStationApMode.name: bsnMobileStationApMode
bsnMobileStationApMode.description: Mode of the AP to which the Mobile Station is associated.

bsnMobileStationVlanId.name: bsnMobileStationVlanId
bsnMobileStationVlanId.description: Vlan ID of the Interface to which the client is associated.

bsnMobileStationPolicyType.name: bsnMobileStationPolicyType
bsnMobileStationPolicyType.description: Mode of the AP to which the Mobile Station is associated.

bsnMobileStationEncryptionCypher.name: bsnMobileStationEncryptionCypher
bsnMobileStationEncryptionCypher.description: Mode of the AP to which the Mobile Station is associated.

bsnMobileStationEapType.name: bsnMobileStationEapType
bsnMobileStationEapType.description: Mode of the AP to which the Mobile Station is associated.

bsnMobileStationCcxVersion.name: bsnMobileStationCcxVersion
bsnMobileStationCcxVersion.description: Represents the Cisco Compatible Extensions (CCX) Version the client is using for communication with the AP.

bsnMobileStationE2eVersion.name: bsnMobileStationE2eVersion
bsnMobileStationE2eVersion.description: Represents the End-2-End Version the client is using for communication with the AP.

bsnMobileStationStatusCode.name: bsnMobileStationStatusCode
bsnMobileStationStatusCode.description: Status Code of the Mobile Station

bsnMobileStationByIpTable.name: bsnMobileStationByIpTable
bsnMobileStationByIpTable.description: Mobile Station Table indexed by bsnMobileStationByIpAddress. NOTE: This is just to facilitate the search of mobile stations based on IP Address. Doing a get without the index doesn't return anything. (Mobile Station is better referred to as Client in the current releases.)

bsnMobileStationByIpAddress.name: bsnMobileStationByIpAddress
bsnMobileStationByIpAddress.description: IP Address of the Mobile Station

bsnMobileStationByIpMacAddress.name: bsnMobileStationByIpMacAddress
bsnMobileStationByIpMacAddress.description: 802.11 Mac Address of the Mobile Station.

bsnMobileStationByUsernameTable.name: bsnMobileStationByUsernameTable
bsnMobileStationByUsernameTable.description: Mobile Station Table indexed by the Mobile Station Username and MAC Address. NOTE: This is just to facilitate the search of mobile stations based on User Name. Doing a get without the username doesn't return anything. (Mobile Station is better referred to as Client in the current releases.)

bsnMobileStationByUserMacAddress.name: bsnMobileStationByUserMacAddress
bsnMobileStationByUserMacAddress.description: 802.11 Mac Address of the Mobile Station.

bsnMobileStationPerRadioPerVapTable.name: bsnMobileStationPerRadioPerVapTable
bsnMobileStationPerRadioPerVapTable.description: Mobile Station Per Radio Per VAP(WLAN) Table. This table lists all Mobile Stations on a particular Airespace AP Interface for a particular ESS(Wlan). It only lists MAC Addresses. Further details for a Mobile Station can be found from bsnMobileStationTable once the MAC Address is knonwn. (Mobile Station is better referred to as Client in the current releases.)

bsnMobileStationPerRadioPerVapIndex.name: bsnMobileStationPerRadioPerVapIndex
bsnMobileStationPerRadioPerVapIndex.description: The index of Mobile Station. The index starts from 1 and goes upto the total number of Mobile Stations on Airespace Radio Interface for a specific ESS (Wlan).

bsnMobileStationMacAddr.name: bsnMobileStationMacAddr
bsnMobileStationMacAddr.description: The MAC Address of Mobile Station.

bsnMobileStationStatsTable.name: bsnMobileStationStatsTable
bsnMobileStationStatsTable.description: Mobile Station Statistics Table. (Mobile Station is better referred to as Client in the current releases.)

bsnMobileStationRSSI.name: bsnMobileStationRSSI
bsnMobileStationRSSI.description: Average packet RSSI for the Mobile Station.

bsnMobileStationPolicyErrors.name: bsnMobileStationPolicyErrors
bsnMobileStationPolicyErrors.description: Number of Policy Errors for Mobile Station

bsnMobileStationSnr.name: bsnMobileStationSnr
bsnMobileStationSnr.description: Signal to noise Ratio of the Mobile Station.

bsnMobileStationExtStatsTable.name: bsnMobileStationExtStatsTable
bsnMobileStationExtStatsTable.description: This table was supported only by indoor mesh AP -cisco 1000. As this AP is not supported after 4.2.x.x. This table has been marked obsolete. Mobile Station Extended Statistics Table. (Mobile Station is better referred to as Client in the current releases.)

bsnMobileStationSampleTime.name: bsnMobileStationSampleTime
bsnMobileStationSampleTime.description: Time stats were sampled as seconds since the epoch.

bsnMobileStationTxExcessiveRetries.name: bsnMobileStationTxExcessiveRetries
bsnMobileStationTxExcessiveRetries.description: Tx packets dropped due to excessive retries.

bsnMobileStationTxFiltered.name: bsnMobileStationTxFiltered
bsnMobileStationTxFiltered.description: Tx packets dropped by the built-in Tx filter

bsnMobileStationRssiDataTable.name: bsnMobileStationRssiDataTable
bsnMobileStationRssiDataTable.description: Mobile Station RSSI data Table indexed by bsnMobileStationMacAddress, bsnMobileStationRssiDataApMacAddress, bsnMobileStationRssiDataApIfSlotId. (Mobile Station is better referred to as Client in the current releases.)

bsnMobileStationRssiDataApMacAddress.name: bsnMobileStationRssiDataApMacAddress
bsnMobileStationRssiDataApMacAddress.description: 802.11 Mac Address of the AP on which Mobile Station is associated.

bsnMobileStationRssiDataApIfSlotId.name: bsnMobileStationRssiDataApIfSlotId
bsnMobileStationRssiDataApIfSlotId.description: SlotId of APIf on which mobile station is associated

bsnMobileStationRssiDataApIfType.name: bsnMobileStationRssiDataApIfType
bsnMobileStationRssiDataApIfType.description: The interface type of the radio that sensed the rssi data.

bsnMobileStationRssiDataApName.name: bsnMobileStationRssiDataApName
bsnMobileStationRssiDataApName.description: The Name of the AP that sensed the rssi data.

bsnMobileStationRssiData.name: bsnMobileStationRssiData
bsnMobileStationRssiData.description: RSSI seen by Airespace AP Interface for the Mobile Station

bsnAPIfPhyAntennaIndex.name: bsnAPIfPhyAntennaIndex
bsnAPIfPhyAntennaIndex.description: Antenna which recived the probe request from client. The antenna which reported the RSSI value for the client. For now value will be 0 to 1, in future it may change.

bsnMobileStationRssiDataLastHeard.name: bsnMobileStationRssiDataLastHeard
bsnMobileStationRssiDataLastHeard.description: No of seconds ago when this RSSI data was recorded.

bsnTagTable.name: bsnTagTable
bsnTagTable.description: RF ID Tag Table indexed by bsnTagDot11MacAddress.

bsnTagDot11MacAddress.name: bsnTagDot11MacAddress
bsnTagDot11MacAddress.description: 802.11 MAC Address of the RF ID Tag.

bsnTagType.name: bsnTagType
bsnTagType.description: Type of the RF ID Tag.

bsnTagTimeInterval.name: bsnTagTimeInterval
bsnTagTimeInterval.description: Time Interval after which the tag transmits data.

bsnTagBatteryStatus.name: bsnTagBatteryStatus
bsnTagBatteryStatus.description: Battery Status of the RF ID Tag.

bsnTagLastReported.name: bsnTagLastReported
bsnTagLastReported.description: No of seconds ago when this tag was heard by any AP.

bsnTagBytesReceived.name: bsnTagBytesReceived
bsnTagBytesReceived.description: Bytes received from an RF ID Tag

bsnTagPacketsReceived.name: bsnTagPacketsReceived
bsnTagPacketsReceived.description: Packets received from an RF ID Tag

bsnTagRssiDataTable.name: bsnTagRssiDataTable
bsnTagRssiDataTable.description: RF ID Tag Detecting AP Table indexed by bsnTagDot11MacAddress, bsnTagRssiDataApMacAddress and bsnTagRssiDataApIfSlotId.

bsnTagRssiDataApMacAddress.name: bsnTagRssiDataApMacAddress
bsnTagRssiDataApMacAddress.description: 802.11 MAC Address of the AP detecting the RF ID Tag.

bsnTagRssiDataApIfSlotId.name: bsnTagRssiDataApIfSlotId
bsnTagRssiDataApIfSlotId.description: Slot Id of the radio on AP detecting the RF ID Tag.

bsnTagRssiDataApIfType.name: bsnTagRssiDataApIfType
bsnTagRssiDataApIfType.description: Interface Type of the radio on AP detecting the RF ID Tag.

bsnTagRssiDataApName.name: bsnTagRssiDataApName
bsnTagRssiDataApName.description: Name of the AP detecting the RF ID Tag.

bsnTagRssiDataLastHeard.name: bsnTagRssiDataLastHeard
bsnTagRssiDataLastHeard.description: No of seconds ago when this tag was heard by this detecting AP.

bsnTagRssiData.name: bsnTagRssiData
bsnTagRssiData.description: RSSI of the RF ID Tag as seen by the radio on this detecting AP.

bsnTagRssiDataSnr.name: bsnTagRssiDataSnr
bsnTagRssiDataSnr.description: SNR of the RF ID tag as seen by the radio on this detecting AP.

bsnWatchListClientTable.name: bsnWatchListClientTable
bsnWatchListClientTable.description: Table of watch listed clients. When clients are added to this table by username or MAC address, ACS collects data for them to show trend reports. The switch generates Client Association and Client Authentication traps for the watch listed clients.The watch list feature can be enbaled or diabled by the bsnWatchListFeatureEnable flag on the switch.

bsnWatchListClientKey.name: bsnWatchListClientKey
bsnWatchListClientKey.description: MAC Address or User Name of Client that is to be added to the watch list.

bsnWatchListClientType.name: bsnWatchListClientType
bsnWatchListClientType.description: The type of the watch list client entry. The entry can be created by Client MAC Address or by Username.

bsnWatchListClientRowStatus.name: bsnWatchListClientRowStatus
bsnWatchListClientRowStatus.description: A row status type for the bsnWatchListClientEntry

bsnRogueAPTable.name: bsnRogueAPTable
bsnRogueAPTable.description: Rogue Table. This table lists all the Rogue APs detected by Airespace APs.

bsnRogueAPTotalDetectingAPs.name: bsnRogueAPTotalDetectingAPs
bsnRogueAPTotalDetectingAPs.description: Total number of Airespace APs that detected this rogue.

bsnRogueAPFirstReported.name: bsnRogueAPFirstReported
bsnRogueAPFirstReported.description: Time Stamp when this Rogue was First Detected.

bsnRogueAPLastReported.name: bsnRogueAPLastReported
bsnRogueAPLastReported.description: Time Stamp when this Rogue was Last Detected.

bsnRogueAPContainmentLevel.name: bsnRogueAPContainmentLevel
bsnRogueAPContainmentLevel.description: If the state of the rogue is contained, this specifies the level of containment. Higher the level, more the number of detecting APs that are used to contain it. The value must be between 1 to 4 for 'contained' state.

bsnRogueAPType.name: bsnRogueAPType
bsnRogueAPType.description: This attribute specifies if the Rogue is of ad-hoc type or is an AP.

bsnRogueAPOnNetwork.name: bsnRogueAPOnNetwork
bsnRogueAPOnNetwork.description: This attribute specifies if the Rogue is on Wired Network or not.

bsnRogueAPTotalClients.name: bsnRogueAPTotalClients
bsnRogueAPTotalClients.description: Total number of Clients detected on this rogue.

bsnRogueAPMaxDetectedRSSI.name: bsnRogueAPMaxDetectedRSSI
bsnRogueAPMaxDetectedRSSI.description: This is the max RSSI value of all the detctecting APs, which have detected this rogue.

bsnRogueAPSSID.name: bsnRogueAPSSID
bsnRogueAPSSID.description: This is the SSID of the rogue detected by Access Point, which has max RSSI value of all the detectecting APs of this rogue.

bsnRogueAPDetectingAPRadioType.name: bsnRogueAPDetectingAPRadioType
bsnRogueAPDetectingAPRadioType.description: Radio type of detecting APs. If the radio type is detected by dot11bg radio or dot11a radio or both.

bsnRogueAPDetectingAPMacAddress.name: bsnRogueAPDetectingAPMacAddress
bsnRogueAPDetectingAPMacAddress.description: MAC Address of of detecting AP which received max RSSI

bsnRogueAPMaxRssiRadioType.name: bsnRogueAPMaxRssiRadioType
bsnRogueAPMaxRssiRadioType.description: The radio type of detecting AP which received max RSSI value.

bsnRogueAPState.name: bsnRogueAPState
bsnRogueAPState.description: This attribute is use to specify the state in which the Rogue AP is user can set the Rogue AP in alert, known or acknowledge state. Alert state means Rogue AP can be a potential threat. Trap will be sent out to trap recipients. Known state means its just internal AP which is not on the same Switch. Acknowledge state means an external AP whose existence is acceptable and not a threat (probably some other company's AP). Contained means containement is initiated and ongoing. Threat is usually the state when the rogue is found on wired network. known(4), knownContained(9) and trustedMissing(10) will appear in known rogue list. known rogues can be pre provisioned and known rogues state can be changed to alert(2)

bsnRogueAPClassType.name: bsnRogueAPClassType
bsnRogueAPClassType.description: The AP class type of the client detected.

bsnRogueAPChannel.name: bsnRogueAPChannel
bsnRogueAPChannel.description: This is the channel number of the last detecting APs, which has detected this rogue.

bsnRogueAPDetectingAPName.name: bsnRogueAPDetectingAPName
bsnRogueAPDetectingAPName.description: AP name of the detecting AP which received max RSSI

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPTable.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPTable
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPTable.description: Rogue Station Table. This table lists all the Airespace AP Interfaces that detected a particular Rogue.

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPMacAddress.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPMacAddress
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPMacAddress.description: MAC Address of Airespace AP Interface that Detected the Rogue.

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPSlotId.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPSlotId
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPSlotId.description: The slot ID of the Airespace AP Interface that detected the Rogue.

bsnRogueAPRadioType.name: bsnRogueAPRadioType
bsnRogueAPRadioType.description: The Airespace AP Interface type that detected the Rogue.

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPName.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPName
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPName.description: Name of Airespace AP Interface that detected the Rogue.

bsnRogueAPChannelNumber.name: bsnRogueAPChannelNumber
bsnRogueAPChannelNumber.description: The advertised Channel Number of the Airespace AP Interface picked up from the Rogue.

bsnRogueAPSsid.name: bsnRogueAPSsid
bsnRogueAPSsid.description: The SSID Advertised by Rogue Station.

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPRSSI.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPRSSI
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPRSSI.description: Rogue RSSI as seen by Airespace AP Interface.

bsnRogueAPContainmentMode.name: bsnRogueAPContainmentMode
bsnRogueAPContainmentMode.description: If the rogue is in 'contained' state, this attribute shows the containment mode used by the AP.

bsnRogueAPContainmentChannelCount.name: bsnRogueAPContainmentChannelCount
bsnRogueAPContainmentChannelCount.description: The number of channels used for rogue containment.

bsnRogueAPContainmentChannels.name: bsnRogueAPContainmentChannels
bsnRogueAPContainmentChannels.description: This is the comma separated string of channels used for rogue containment.

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPLastHeard.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPLastHeard
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPLastHeard.description: No of seconds ago when this Rogue was last heard by this AP.

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPWepMode.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPWepMode
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPWepMode.description: The WEP mode on this detecting AP.

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPPreamble.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPPreamble
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPPreamble.description: The Preamble on this detecting AP.

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPWpaMode.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPWpaMode
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPWpaMode.description: The WPA mode on this detecting AP.

bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPSNR.name: bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPSNR
bsnRogueAPAirespaceAPSNR.description: SNR seen by Airespace AP Interface from Rogue

bsnRogueAPChannelWidth.name: bsnRogueAPChannelWidth
bsnRogueAPChannelWidth.description: This object represents the channel width of the rogue.

bsnRogueClientPerRogueAPTable.name: bsnRogueClientPerRogueAPTable
bsnRogueClientPerRogueAPTable.description: Rogue Clients for each rogue. This table lists all Rogue Clients on a particular Rogue.

bsnRogueAPDot11MacAddr.name: bsnRogueAPDot11MacAddr
bsnRogueAPDot11MacAddr.description: The MAC Address of the Rogue AP.

bsnRogueClientDot11MacAddr.name: bsnRogueClientDot11MacAddr
bsnRogueClientDot11MacAddr.description: MAC Address of the Rogue Client.

bsnRogueClientTable.name: bsnRogueClientTable
bsnRogueClientTable.description: Rogue Client Table. This table lists all the Rogue Clients detected by Airespace APs.

bsnRogueClientTotalDetectingAPs.name: bsnRogueClientTotalDetectingAPs
bsnRogueClientTotalDetectingAPs.description: Total number of Airespace APs that detected this rogue.

bsnRogueClientFirstReported.name: bsnRogueClientFirstReported
bsnRogueClientFirstReported.description: Time Stamp when this Rogue was First Detected.

bsnRogueClientLastReported.name: bsnRogueClientLastReported
bsnRogueClientLastReported.description: Time Stamp when this Rogue was Last Detected.

bsnRogueClientBSSID.name: bsnRogueClientBSSID
bsnRogueClientBSSID.description: This attribute specifies BSSID of the Rogue Client.

bsnRogueClientContainmentLevel.name: bsnRogueClientContainmentLevel
bsnRogueClientContainmentLevel.description: If the state of the rogue is contained, this specifies the level of containment. Higher the level, more the number of detecting APs that are used to contain it. The value must be between 1 to 4 for 'contained' state.

bsnRogueClientLastHeard.name: bsnRogueClientLastHeard
bsnRogueClientLastHeard.description: Number of seconds ago this rogue client was detected.

bsnRogueClientState.name: bsnRogueClientState
bsnRogueClientState.description: This attribute is use to specify the state in which the Rogue AP is. User can set the Rogue Client in alert,known or acknowledge state. Alert state means Rogue Client can be a potential i threat.Trap will be sent out to trap recipients. Known state means its just internal Client which is not on the same Switch. Acknowledge state means an external Client whose existence is acceptable and not a threat (probably some other company's AP). Contained means containement is initiated and ongoing

bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPTable.name: bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPTable
bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPTable.description: Rogue Station Table. This table lists all the Airespace AP Interface that detected a particular Rogue.

bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPMacAddress.name: bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPMacAddress
bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPMacAddress.description: Mac Address of Airespace AP Interface that Detected the Rogue.

bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPSlotId.name: bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPSlotId
bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPSlotId.description: The slotId of the Airespace AP Interface that detected the Rogue.

bsnRogueClientRadioType.name: bsnRogueClientRadioType
bsnRogueClientRadioType.description: The advertised SSID that the Airespace AP Interface picked up from the Rogue.

bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPName.name: bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPName
bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPName.description: Name of Airespace AP Interface that detected the Rogue.

bsnRogueClientChannelNumber.name: bsnRogueClientChannelNumber
bsnRogueClientChannelNumber.description: The advertised Channel Number of that the Airespace AP Interface picked up from the Rogue.

bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPRSSI.name: bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPRSSI
bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPRSSI.description: RSSI seen by Airespace AP Interface from the Rogue

bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPLastHeard.name: bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPLastHeard
bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPLastHeard.description: No of seconds ago when this Rogue was last heard by this AP.

bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPSNR.name: bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPSNR
bsnRogueClientAirespaceAPSNR.description: SNR seen by Airespace AP Interface from Rogue

bsnThirdPartyAPTable.name: bsnThirdPartyAPTable
bsnThirdPartyAPTable.description: Third Party Access Point Table. An entry needs to be configured in this table for a third party access point that needs to be supported by the Switch. Note: A third party ESS (Wlan) with ID 17 should be created in bsnDot11EssTable before adding entries here. Please also note that ACS currently supports only Aironet 350, 1200 and Orinoco 2000 Access Points as third party APs.

bsnThirdPartyAPMacAddress.name: bsnThirdPartyAPMacAddress
bsnThirdPartyAPMacAddress.description: MAC Address of Third Party Access Point which is connected directly to this Airespace Switch.

bsnThirdPartyAPInterface.name: bsnThirdPartyAPInterface
bsnThirdPartyAPInterface.description: Interface(Port Number) to which the Third Party AP is connected.

bsnThirdPartyAPIpAddress.name: bsnThirdPartyAPIpAddress
bsnThirdPartyAPIpAddress.description: Static IP address of the 3rd Party AP, 0.0.0.0 indicating x its using DHCP

bsnThirdPartyAP802Dot1XRequired.name: bsnThirdPartyAP802Dot1XRequired
bsnThirdPartyAP802Dot1XRequired.description: If 802.1X is required for the 3rd Party AP

bsnThirdPartyAPMirrorMode.name: bsnThirdPartyAPMirrorMode
bsnThirdPartyAPMirrorMode.description: If enabled, then data from all the foreign AP users and all the foreign APs on this APs port will be mirrored. These clients are dynamically added to the switch's mirrored MAC list.

bsnAPTable.name: bsnAPTable
bsnAPTable.description: Table of Airespace APs managed by this Airespace Switch.

bsnAPDot3MacAddress.name: bsnAPDot3MacAddress
bsnAPDot3MacAddress.description: The MAC address of an AP.

bsnAPNumOfSlots.name: bsnAPNumOfSlots
bsnAPNumOfSlots.description: Number of Radio Interfaces on the Airespace AP. Currently maximum two interfaces are supported. One would be of type 802.11a and other of type 802.11b/g.

bsnAPName.name: bsnAPName
bsnAPName.description: Name assigned to this AP. If an AP is not configured its factory default name will be ap:<last three byte of MACAddress> eg. ap:af:12:be

bsnAPLocation.name: bsnAPLocation
bsnAPLocation.description: User specified location of this AP. While configuring AP, user should specify a location for the AP so that its easy to figure out for some one where the AP is located.

bsnAPOperationStatus.name: bsnAPOperationStatus
bsnAPOperationStatus.description: Operation State of the AP. When AP associates with the Airespace Switch its state will be associated. When Airespace AP is disassociated from the Switch, its state will be disassociating. The state is downloading when the AP is downloading its firmware.

bsnAPSoftwareVersion.name: bsnAPSoftwareVersion
bsnAPSoftwareVersion.description: Major Minor Software Version of AP

bsnAPBootVersion.name: bsnAPBootVersion
bsnAPBootVersion.description: Major Minor Boot Version of AP

bsnAPPrimaryMwarName.name: bsnAPPrimaryMwarName
bsnAPPrimaryMwarName.description: sysName of the Airespace Switch which is suppose to be the Primary MWAR(switch) of the AP with which AP should associate. This work when AP is not directly connected to Airespace Switch, it tries to find Primary Switch and associates with it. If this attribute is left empty or AP is not able to find the Airespace Switch with this name, then it will associate with Secondary Switch.

bsnAPReset.name: bsnAPReset
bsnAPReset.description: Set this attribute to reset the AP. When it comes up it will try to associate with the Primary Switch if that is set, else it will associate with the Master Switch. Reading this attribute will always return 0

bsnAPStatsTimer.name: bsnAPStatsTimer
bsnAPStatsTimer.description: Configures the time interval in secs after which bsnAPDot11Counters Stats is sent from AP to Switch. If not configured this value is 0 which means never send the stats.

bsnAPPortNumber.name: bsnAPPortNumber
bsnAPPortNumber.description: Port on the Switch on which this APs traffic is coming through.

bsnAPClearConfig.name: bsnAPClearConfig
bsnAPClearConfig.description: Set this attribute to clear AP configuration and reset it to factory defaults. A value of clearAll(2) resets all values to factory defaults. A value of clear(1) resets all values except static IP of the AP. Reading this attribute will always return 0

bsnApIpAddress.name: bsnApIpAddress
bsnApIpAddress.description: IP address of the AP. This will not be available when the switch is operating in the Layer2 mode. In this case, the attribute will return 0 as value.

bsnAPMirrorMode.name: bsnAPMirrorMode
bsnAPMirrorMode.description: If enabled, then this AP's Client's Data is mirrored and this AP's clients are dynamically added to the switch's mirrored MAC list.

bsnAPRemoteModeSupport.name: bsnAPRemoteModeSupport
bsnAPRemoteModeSupport.description: This specifies if the the Remote Mode is supported on this AP or not. If supported user can set bsnAPMonitorOnlyMode to remote. Otherwise not.

bsnAPType.name: bsnAPType
bsnAPType.description: This is the model of the AP in enumeration.

bsnAPSecondaryMwarName.name: bsnAPSecondaryMwarName
bsnAPSecondaryMwarName.description: sysName of the Airespace Switch which is suppose to be the Secondary MWAR(switch) of the AP with which AP should associate if Primary Switch(configured through bsnAPPrimaryMwarName) is not available. If primary and secondary switches are not available then AP will associate with the tertiary switch.

bsnAPTertiaryMwarName.name: bsnAPTertiaryMwarName
bsnAPTertiaryMwarName.description: sysName of the Airespace Switch which is suppose to be the Tertiary MWAR(switch) of the AP with which AP should associate. If primary,secondary and tertiary switch are not available then it will associate with Master Switch.

bsnAPIsStaticIP.name: bsnAPIsStaticIP
bsnAPIsStaticIP.description: This flag when disabled implies that AP will use DHCP to get the IP address. However, if it is enabled, then user should enter the IPAddress, Netmask and Gateway.

bsnAPNetmask.name: bsnAPNetmask
bsnAPNetmask.description: The Netmask of the IP address of the AP.

bsnAPStaticIPAddress.name: bsnAPStaticIPAddress
bsnAPStaticIPAddress.description: The Static IP-Address configuration for the AP. This can only be changed when the LWAPP mode is in Layer-3.

bsnAPBridgingSupport.name: bsnAPBridgingSupport
bsnAPBridgingSupport.description: This specifies if this AP is a Bridging AP. Bridging APs can be used in Bridging or Mesh network configurations.

bsnAPGroupVlanName.name: bsnAPGroupVlanName
bsnAPGroupVlanName.description: The AP Group to which this AP has been associated with. If it is empty, then no AP Group overriding has been set.

bsnAPIOSVersion.name: bsnAPIOSVersion
bsnAPIOSVersion.description: IOS Version of IOS Cisco AP. Zero length string will be returned for other APs

bsnAPCertificateType.name: bsnAPCertificateType
bsnAPCertificateType.description: Enum values denoting AP Certificate Type. 1 : manufactureinstalled : Manufacture Installed Certificate type (MIC). 2 : selfsigned : Self Signed Certificate type (SSC). 3 : localsignificance : Local Significance.

bsnAPEthernetMacAddress.name: bsnAPEthernetMacAddress
bsnAPEthernetMacAddress.description: The Ethernet MAC address of the AP.

bsnAPIfTable.name: bsnAPIfTable
bsnAPIfTable.description: Each entry represents an 802.11 interface in an Airespace AP.

bsnAPIfType.name: bsnAPIfType
bsnAPIfType.description: The type of this interface. dot11b also implies 802.11b/g.

bsnAPIfPhyChannelAssignment.name: bsnAPIfPhyChannelAssignment
bsnAPIfPhyChannelAssignment.description: If this value is true, then bsnAPDot11CurrentChannel in bsnAPIfDot11PhyDSSSTable is assigned by dynamic algorithm and is read-only.

bsnAPIfPhyChannelNumber.name: bsnAPIfPhyChannelNumber
bsnAPIfPhyChannelNumber.description: Current channel number of the AP Interface. Channel numbers will be from 1 to 14 for 802.11b interface type. Channel numbers will be from 34 to 173 for 802.11a interface type. Allowed channel numbers also depends on the current Country Code set in the Switch. This attribute cannot be set unless bsnAPIfPhyChannelAssignment is set to customized else this attribute gets assigned by dynamic algorithm.

bsnAPIfPhyTxPowerControl.name: bsnAPIfPhyTxPowerControl
bsnAPIfPhyTxPowerControl.description: If this value is true, then bsnAPIfPhyTxPowerLevel is assigned by dynamic algorithm and is read-only.

bsnAPIfPhyTxPowerLevel.name: bsnAPIfPhyTxPowerLevel
bsnAPIfPhyTxPowerLevel.description: The TxPowerLevel currently being used to transmit data. Some PHYs also use this value to determine the receiver sensitivity requirements for CCA. Valid values are between 1 to 8,depnding on what radio, and this attribute can be set only if bsnAPIfPhyTxPowerControl is set to customized.

bsnAPIfPhyAntennaMode.name: bsnAPIfPhyAntennaMode
bsnAPIfPhyAntennaMode.description: Antenna Mode of the AP Interface. For 802.11a this attribute will always be omni for now. This attribute doesn't apply to interface of type 802.11b.

bsnAPIfPhyAntennaType.name: bsnAPIfPhyAntennaType
bsnAPIfPhyAntennaType.description: This attribute specified if the Antenna currently used by AP Radio is internal or external. For 802.11a the antenna is always internal. For 802.11b you can set antenna type to be external or internal.

bsnAPIfPhyAntennaDiversity.name: bsnAPIfPhyAntennaDiversity
bsnAPIfPhyAntennaDiversity.description: Diversity doesn't apply to AP Radio of type 802.11a. For 802.11b you can set it to connectorA, connectorB or enabled.

bsnAPIfCellSiteConfigId.name: bsnAPIfCellSiteConfigId
bsnAPIfCellSiteConfigId.description: In a cell site configuration, this would be the cell Id of this AP Interface

bsnAPIfNumberOfVaps.name: bsnAPIfNumberOfVaps
bsnAPIfNumberOfVaps.description: Number of WLANs currently active on this AP Interface.

bsnAPIfPortNumber.name: bsnAPIfPortNumber
bsnAPIfPortNumber.description: Port number on Airespace Switch on which the traffic from this AP interface is received.

bsnAPIfPhyAntennaOptions.name: bsnAPIfPhyAntennaOptions
bsnAPIfPhyAntennaOptions.description: This attribute specifies the Antenna types supported by the AP Radio whether it is internal or external or both. internalAndExternal(0)- internal and external antenna for both 11a and 11b internal(1) - only internal antenna is allowed. siacAp- 11b internal and 11a external external - only external antenna is allowed for 11a and 11b ext11bInt11a - external antenna for 11b and internal antenna for 11a.

bsnApIfNoOfUsers.name: bsnApIfNoOfUsers
bsnApIfNoOfUsers.description: No of Users associated with this radio.

bsnAPIfWlanOverride.name: bsnAPIfWlanOverride
bsnAPIfWlanOverride.description: This flag when disabled implies that all WLANs are available from this radio. However, if this is enabled, then only those WLANs that appear in the bsnApIfWlanOverrideTable will be available from this radio.

bsnAPIfPacketsSniffingFeature.name: bsnAPIfPacketsSniffingFeature
bsnAPIfPacketsSniffingFeature.description: This flag when enabled implies that AP will sniff the 802.11a/bg packets. However, if it is enabled, then user should enter the server-ip-address on which Airopeek is running and the 802.11a/bg-channel-number to be sniffed. The above feature will work only when AP is in 'Sniffer' mode.

bsnAPIfSniffChannel.name: bsnAPIfSniffChannel
bsnAPIfSniffChannel.description: This the 802.11a/bg-channel-number on which AP will sniff the packets.

bsnAPIfSniffServerIPAddress.name: bsnAPIfSniffServerIPAddress
bsnAPIfSniffServerIPAddress.description: The machine ip address on which Airopeek application is running.

bsnAPIfAntennaGain.name: bsnAPIfAntennaGain
bsnAPIfAntennaGain.description: Represents antenna gain in multiple of 0.5 dBi. An integer value 4 means 4 x 0.5 = 2 dBi of gain

bsnAPIfChannelList.name: bsnAPIfChannelList
bsnAPIfChannelList.description: List of comma separated channels supported by this radio.

bsnAPIfAbsolutePowerList.name: bsnAPIfAbsolutePowerList
bsnAPIfAbsolutePowerList.description: List of comma separated absolute power levels supported by this radio.

bsnAPIfRegulatoryDomainSupport.name: bsnAPIfRegulatoryDomainSupport
bsnAPIfRegulatoryDomainSupport.description: If the regulatory domain on radio is supported or notSupported on the controller

bsnAPIfWlanOverrideTable.name: bsnAPIfWlanOverrideTable
bsnAPIfWlanOverrideTable.description: Each entry represents an SSID added to the AP when the attribute bsnAPIfWlanOverride on the radio is enabled. This means only those WLANs on the switch that are added to this table will be available on such a radio.

bsnAPIfWlanOverrideId.name: bsnAPIfWlanOverrideId
bsnAPIfWlanOverrideId.description: Index of the WLAN (bsnDot11EssIndex) added to the radio. Airespace Switch supports 16 Airespace WLANs so index will be from 1 to 16.

bsnAPIfWlanOverrideSsid.name: bsnAPIfWlanOverrideSsid
bsnAPIfWlanOverrideSsid.description: SSID assigned to the override WLAN.

bsnAPIfWlanOverrideRowStatus.name: bsnAPIfWlanOverrideRowStatus
bsnAPIfWlanOverrideRowStatus.description: A row status type for the bsnAPIfWlanOverrideEntry

bsnAPIfSmtParamTable.name: bsnAPIfSmtParamTable
bsnAPIfSmtParamTable.description: Each entry represents SMT parameters on an 802.11 interface of an Airespace AP.

bsnAPIfDot11BeaconPeriod.name: bsnAPIfDot11BeaconPeriod
bsnAPIfDot11BeaconPeriod.description: This attribute shall specify the number of TU that a AP Interface shall use for scheduling Beacon tranmissions. This value is transmitted in Beacon and Probe Response frames.

bsnAPIfDot11MediumOccupancyLimit.name: bsnAPIfDot11MediumOccupancyLimit
bsnAPIfDot11MediumOccupancyLimit.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum amount of time, in TU, that a point coordinator may control the usage of the wireless medium without relinquishing control for long enough to allow at least one instance of DCF access to the medium. The default value of this attribute shall be 100, and the maximum value shall be 1000.

bsnAPIfDot11CFPPeriod.name: bsnAPIfDot11CFPPeriod
bsnAPIfDot11CFPPeriod.description: The attribute shall describe the number of DTIM intervals between the start of CFPs. It is modified by MLME-START.request primitive.

bsnAPIfDot11CFPMaxDuration.name: bsnAPIfDot11CFPMaxDuration
bsnAPIfDot11CFPMaxDuration.description: The attribute shall describe the maximum duration of the CFP in TU that may be generated by the PCF. It is modified by MLME-START.request primitive.

bsnAPIfDot11OperationalRateSet.name: bsnAPIfDot11OperationalRateSet
bsnAPIfDot11OperationalRateSet.description: This attribute shall specify the set of data rates at which the AP Interface may transmit data. Each octet contains a value representing a rate. Each rate shall be within the range from 2 to 127, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500 kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s, and shall be supported (as indicated in the supported rates table) for receiving data. This value is reported in transmitted Beacon, Probe Request, Probe Response, Association Request, Association Response, Reassociation Request, and Reassociation Response frames, and is used to determine whether a BSS with which the AP Interface desires to synchronize is suitable. It is also used when starting a BSS, as specified in 10.3.

bsnAPIfDot11DTIMPeriod.name: bsnAPIfDot11DTIMPeriod
bsnAPIfDot11DTIMPeriod.description: This attribute shall specify the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmission of Beacons frames containing a TIM element whose DTIM Count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the DTIM Period field of Beacon frames.

bsnAPIfDot11MultiDomainCapabilityImpleme.name: bsnAPIfDot11MultiDomainCapabilityImplemented
bsnAPIfDot11MultiDomainCapabilityImpleme.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the AP Interface implementation is capable of supporting multiple regulatory domains. The capability is disabled, otherwise. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

bsnAPIfDot11MultiDomainCapabilityEnabled.name: bsnAPIfDot11MultiDomainCapabilityEnabled
bsnAPIfDot11MultiDomainCapabilityEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the capability of the AP Interface to operate in multiple regulatory domains is enabled. The capability is disabled, otherwise. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

bsnAPIfDot11CountryString.name: bsnAPIfDot11CountryString
bsnAPIfDot11CountryString.description: This attribute identifies the country in which the AP Interface is operating. The first two octets of this string is the two character country code as described in document ISO/IEC 3166-1. The third octet shall be one of the following: 1. an ASCII space character, if the regulations under which the AP Interface is operating encompass all environments in the country, 2. an ASCII 'O' character, if the regulations under which the AP Interface is operating are for an Outdoor environment only, or 3. an ASCII 'I' character, if the regulations under which the AP Interface is operating are for an Indoor environment only.

bsnAPIfDot11SmtParamsConfigType.name: bsnAPIfDot11SmtParamsConfigType
bsnAPIfDot11SmtParamsConfigType.description: This attribute suggests if the Station parameters for this radio are automatically set or have been customized.

bsnAPIfDot11BSSID.name: bsnAPIfDot11BSSID
bsnAPIfDot11BSSID.description: BSSID of this AP config which would be the MAC Address of AP

bsnAPIfMultiDomainCapabilityTable.name: bsnAPIfMultiDomainCapabilityTable
bsnAPIfMultiDomainCapabilityTable.description: Each entry represents an 803.2 or an 802.11 interface in an Airespace AP.

bsnAPIfMultiDomainCapabilityEntry.name: bsnAPIfMultiDomainCapabilityEntry
bsnAPIfMultiDomainCapabilityEntry.description: Each entry represents an 803.2 or an 802.11 interface in an Airespace AP.

bsnAPIfDot11MaximumTransmitPowerLevel.name: bsnAPIfDot11MaximumTransmitPowerLevel
bsnAPIfDot11MaximumTransmitPowerLevel.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum transmit power, in dBm, allowed in the subband for the associated domain country string. The default value of this attribute shall be zero.

bsnAPIfDot11FirstChannelNumber.name: bsnAPIfDot11FirstChannelNumber
bsnAPIfDot11FirstChannelNumber.description: This attribute shall indicate the value of the lowest channel number in the subband for the associated domain country string. The default value of this attribute shall be zero.

bsnAPIfDot11NumberofChannels.name: bsnAPIfDot11NumberofChannels
bsnAPIfDot11NumberofChannels.description: This attribute shall indicate the value of the total number of channels allowed in the subband for the associated domain country string. The default value of this attribute shall be zero.

bsnAPIfMacOperationParamTable.name: bsnAPIfMacOperationParamTable
bsnAPIfMacOperationParamTable.description: Group contains MAC attributes pertaining to the operation of the MAC. These would be read only attributes as they would be updated by RRM Dynamic Algorithm. If user needs to configure them then they can only be configured globally

bsnAPIfMacOperationParamEntry.name: bsnAPIfMacOperationParamEntry
bsnAPIfMacOperationParamEntry.description: An entry in the bsnAPIfMacOperationParamEntry Table. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId.

bsnAPIfDot11MacRTSThreshold.name: bsnAPIfDot11MacRTSThreshold
bsnAPIfDot11MacRTSThreshold.description: If bsnAPIfMacParamsAutomaticOn is true then this is read only parameter updated by RRM dynamic algorithm

bsnAPIfDot11MacShortRetryLimit.name: bsnAPIfDot11MacShortRetryLimit
bsnAPIfDot11MacShortRetryLimit.description: If bsnAPIfMacParamsAutomaticOn is true then this is read only parameter updated by RRM dynamic algorithm

bsnAPIfDot11MacLongRetryLimit.name: bsnAPIfDot11MacLongRetryLimit
bsnAPIfDot11MacLongRetryLimit.description: If bsnAPIfMacParamsAutomaticOn is true then this is read only parameter updated by RRM dynamic algorithm

bsnAPIfDot11MacFragmentationThreshold.name: bsnAPIfDot11MacFragmentationThreshold
bsnAPIfDot11MacFragmentationThreshold.description: If bsnAPIfMacParamsAutomaticOn is true then this is read only parameter updated by RRM dynamic algorithm

bsnAPIfDot11MacMaxTransmitMSDULifetime.name: bsnAPIfDot11MacMaxTransmitMSDULifetime
bsnAPIfDot11MacMaxTransmitMSDULifetime.description: If bsnAPIfMacParamsAutomaticOn is true then this is read only parameter updated by RRM dynamic algorithm

bsnAPIfDot11MacParamsConfigType.name: bsnAPIfDot11MacParamsConfigType
bsnAPIfDot11MacParamsConfigType.description: This attribute suggests if the MAC parameters for this radio are automatically set or have been customized.

bsnAPIfDot11MacMaxReceiveLifetime.name: bsnAPIfDot11MacMaxReceiveLifetime
bsnAPIfDot11MacMaxReceiveLifetime.description: If bsnAPIfMacParamsAutomaticOn is true then this is read only parameter updated by RRM dynamic algorithm

bsnAPIfDot11CountersTable.name: bsnAPIfDot11CountersTable
bsnAPIfDot11CountersTable.description: Group containing attributes that are MAC counters. Each instance represents counters on a AP dot11 interface

bsnAPIfDot11CountersEntry.name: bsnAPIfDot11CountersEntry
bsnAPIfDot11CountersEntry.description: An entry in the dot11CountersEntry Table. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress and bsnAPIfSlotId

bsnAPIfDot11TransmittedFragmentCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11TransmittedFragmentCount
bsnAPIfDot11TransmittedFragmentCount.description: This counter shall be incremented for an acknowledged MPDU with an individual address in the address 1 field or an MPDU with a multicast address in the address 1 field of type Data or Management.

bsnAPIfDot11MulticastTransmittedFrameCou.name: bsnAPIfDot11MulticastTransmittedFrameCount
bsnAPIfDot11MulticastTransmittedFrameCou.description: This counter shall increment only when the multicast bit is set in the destination MAC address of a successfully transmitted MSDU. When operating as a STA in an ESS, where these frames are directed to the AP, this implies having received an acknowledgment to all associated MPDUs.

bsnAPIfDot11RetryCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11RetryCount
bsnAPIfDot11RetryCount.description: This counter shall increment when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after one or more retransmissions.

bsnAPIfDot11MultipleRetryCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11MultipleRetryCount
bsnAPIfDot11MultipleRetryCount.description: This counter shall increment when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after more than one retransmission.

bsnAPIfDot11FrameDuplicateCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11FrameDuplicateCount
bsnAPIfDot11FrameDuplicateCount.description: This counter shall increment when a frame is received that the Sequence Control field indicates is a duplicate.

bsnAPIfDot11RTSSuccessCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11RTSSuccessCount
bsnAPIfDot11RTSSuccessCount.description: This counter shall increment when a CTS is received in response to an RTS.

bsnAPIfDot11RTSFailureCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11RTSFailureCount
bsnAPIfDot11RTSFailureCount.description: This counter shall increment when a CTS is not received in response to an RTS.

bsnAPIfDot11ACKFailureCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11ACKFailureCount
bsnAPIfDot11ACKFailureCount.description: This counter shall increment when an ACK is not received when expected.

bsnAPIfDot11ReceivedFragmentCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11ReceivedFragmentCount
bsnAPIfDot11ReceivedFragmentCount.description: This counter shall be incremented for each successfully received MPDU of type Data or Management.

bsnAPIfDot11MulticastReceivedFrameCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11MulticastReceivedFrameCount
bsnAPIfDot11MulticastReceivedFrameCount.description: This counter shall increment when a MSDU is received with the multicast bit set in the destination MAC address.

bsnAPIfDot11FCSErrorCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11FCSErrorCount
bsnAPIfDot11FCSErrorCount.description: This counter shall increment when an FCS error is detected in a received MPDU.

bsnAPIfDot11TransmittedFrameCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11TransmittedFrameCount
bsnAPIfDot11TransmittedFrameCount.description: This counter shall increment for each successfully transmitted MSDU.

bsnAPIfDot11WEPUndecryptableCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11WEPUndecryptableCount
bsnAPIfDot11WEPUndecryptableCount.description: This counter shall increment when a frame is received with the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field set to one and the WEPOn value for the key mapped to the TA's MAC address indicates that the frame should not have been encrypted or that frame is discarded due to the receiving STA not implementing the privacy option.

bsnAPIfDot11FailedCount.name: bsnAPIfDot11FailedCount
bsnAPIfDot11FailedCount.description: This counter shall increment when an MSDU is not transmitted successfully due to the number of transmit attempts exceeding either the bsnAPIfDot11ShortRetryLimit or dot11LongRetryLimit.

bsnAPIfDot11PhyTxPowerTable.name: bsnAPIfDot11PhyTxPowerTable
bsnAPIfDot11PhyTxPowerTable.description: Group of attributes for bsnAPIfDot11PhyTxPowerTable. Implemented as a table indexed on STA ID to allow for multiple instances on an Agent. This table has been deprecated. The level and power can be obtained from bsnAPIfTable(bsnAPIfAbsolutePowerList).

bsnAPIfDot11PhyTxPowerEntry.name: bsnAPIfDot11PhyTxPowerEntry
bsnAPIfDot11PhyTxPowerEntry.description: An entry in the bsnAPIfDot11PhyTxPower Table. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId.

bsnAPIfDot11NumberSupportedPowerLevels.name: bsnAPIfDot11NumberSupportedPowerLevels
bsnAPIfDot11NumberSupportedPowerLevels.description: The number of power levels supported by the PMD. This attribute can have a value of 1 to 8.

bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel1.name: bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel1
bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel1.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL1 in mW. This is also the default power level. It is same as the Maximum power level available on an AP interface.

bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel2.name: bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel2
bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel2.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL2 in mW. It is 1/2 of the Maximum power level available on an AP interface.

bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel3.name: bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel3
bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel3.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL3 in mW. It is 1/4th of the Maximum power level available on an AP interface.

bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel4.name: bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel4
bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel4.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL4 in mW. It is 1/8th of the Maximum power level available on an AP interface.

bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel5.name: bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel5
bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel5.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL5 in mW. It is 1/16th of the Maximum power level available on an AP interface.

bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel6.name: bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel6
bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel6.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL6 in mW. It is 1/32th of the Maximum power level available on an AP interface.

bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel7.name: bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel7
bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel7.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL7 in mW. It is 1/64th of the Maximum power level available on an AP interface.

bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel8.name: bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel8
bsnAPIfDot11TxPowerLevel8.description: The transmit output power for LEVEL8 in mW. It is 1/128th of the Maximum power level available on an AP interface.

bsnAPIfDot11PhyChannelTable.name: bsnAPIfDot11PhyChannelTable
bsnAPIfDot11PhyChannelTable.description: Entry of attributes for bsnAPIfDot11PhyChannelEntry. Implemented as a table indexed on bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId allow for multiple instances on an Agent

bsnAPIfDot11PhyChannelEntry.name: bsnAPIfDot11PhyChannelEntry
bsnAPIfDot11PhyChannelEntry.description: An entry in the bsnAPIfDot11PhyChannelEntry Table. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId.

bsnAPIfDot11CurrentCCAMode.name: bsnAPIfDot11CurrentCCAMode
bsnAPIfDot11CurrentCCAMode.description: The current CCA method in operation.Valid values are: energy detect only (edonly) = 01, carrier sense only (csonly) = 02, carrier sense and energy detect (edandcs)= 04 carrier sense with timer (cswithtimer)= 08 high rate carrier sense and energy detect (hrcsanded)=16.

bsnAPIfDot11EDThreshold.name: bsnAPIfDot11EDThreshold
bsnAPIfDot11EDThreshold.description: The current Energy Detect Threshold being used by the Channel PHY.

bsnAPIfDot11TIThreshold.name: bsnAPIfDot11TIThreshold
bsnAPIfDot11TIThreshold.description: The Threshold being used to detect a busy medium (frequency). CCA shall report a busy medium upon detecting the RSSI above this threshold.

bsnAPIfProfileThresholdConfigTable.name: bsnAPIfProfileThresholdConfigTable
bsnAPIfProfileThresholdConfigTable.description: Table of attributes for various thresholds to be set on each Airespace AP Interface for Load performance profile , interference performance profile and Noise performance profile.

bsnAPIfProfileThresholdConfigEntry.name: bsnAPIfProfileThresholdConfigEntry
bsnAPIfProfileThresholdConfigEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Phy Thresholds Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress and bsnAPIfSlotId

bsnAPIfProfileParamAssignment.name: bsnAPIfProfileParamAssignment
bsnAPIfProfileParamAssignment.description: If this value is automatic then Profile Parameters in bsnRrmDot11aAPProfile at the global level will be used. If this value is customized then Profile Parameters in bsnAPIfProfileThresholdConfig Table will be used and user can customize them per AP.

bsnAPIfForeignInterferenceThreshold.name: bsnAPIfForeignInterferenceThreshold
bsnAPIfForeignInterferenceThreshold.description: foreign interference threshold between 0 and 100 percent.

bsnAPIfForeignNoiseThreshold.name: bsnAPIfForeignNoiseThreshold
bsnAPIfForeignNoiseThreshold.description: foreign noise threshold between -100 and -50 dBm.

bsnAPIfRFUtilizationThreshold.name: bsnAPIfRFUtilizationThreshold
bsnAPIfRFUtilizationThreshold.description: RF utlization threshold between 0 and 100 percent.

bsnAPIfThroughputThreshold.name: bsnAPIfThroughputThreshold
bsnAPIfThroughputThreshold.description: Airespace AP data-rate threshold between 1000 and 100000

bsnAPIfMobilesThreshold.name: bsnAPIfMobilesThreshold
bsnAPIfMobilesThreshold.description: Airespace AP mobiles threshold between 1 and 75

bsnAPIfCoverageThreshold.name: bsnAPIfCoverageThreshold
bsnAPIfCoverageThreshold.description: Airespace AP coverage threshold between 3 and 50

bsnAPIfMobileMinExceptionLevel.name: bsnAPIfMobileMinExceptionLevel
bsnAPIfMobileMinExceptionLevel.description: Airespace AP mobile minimum exception level between 1 and 1000

bsnAPIfCoverageExceptionLevel.name: bsnAPIfCoverageExceptionLevel
bsnAPIfCoverageExceptionLevel.description: Airespace AP coverage exception level between 0 and 100 percent.

bsnAPIfLoadParametersTable.name: bsnAPIfLoadParametersTable
bsnAPIfLoadParametersTable.description: These are RRM performance related read only parameters per Airespace AP

bsnAPIfLoadParametersEntry.name: bsnAPIfLoadParametersEntry
bsnAPIfLoadParametersEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress and bsnAPIfSlotId

bsnAPIfLoadRxUtilization.name: bsnAPIfLoadRxUtilization
bsnAPIfLoadRxUtilization.description: This is the percentage of time the Airespace AP receiver is busy operating on packets. It is a number from 0-100 representing a load from 0 to 1.

bsnAPIfLoadTxUtilization.name: bsnAPIfLoadTxUtilization
bsnAPIfLoadTxUtilization.description: This is the percentage of time the Airespace AP transmitter is busy operating on packets. It is a number from 0-100 representing a load from 0 to 1.

bsnAPIfLoadNumOfClients.name: bsnAPIfLoadNumOfClients
bsnAPIfLoadNumOfClients.description: This is the number of clients attached to this Airespace AP at the last measurement interval(This comes from APF)

bsnAPIfPoorSNRClients.name: bsnAPIfPoorSNRClients
bsnAPIfPoorSNRClients.description: This is the number of clients with poor SNR attached to this Airespace AP at the last measurement interval ( This comes from APF ).

bsnAPIfChannelInterferenceInfoTable.name: bsnAPIfChannelInterferenceInfoTable
