bsnAPIfChannelInterferenceInfoTable.description: This is a table of channel information like interference and noise from other 802.11 networks on each channel.

bsnAPIfChannelInterferenceInfoEntry.name: bsnAPIfChannelInterferenceInfoEntry
bsnAPIfChannelInterferenceInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId

bsnAPIfInterferencePower.name: bsnAPIfInterferencePower
bsnAPIfInterferencePower.description: Power of Interference from other 802.11 networks on this channel

bsnAPIfInterferenceUtilization.name: bsnAPIfInterferenceUtilization
bsnAPIfInterferenceUtilization.description: Interference from other 802.11 networks on this channel

bsnAPIfRadarChannelStatisticsTable.name: bsnAPIfRadarChannelStatisticsTable
bsnAPIfRadarChannelStatisticsTable.description: This is a table of channel information on which radar signal were detected. This will give the list of channels and last heard timestamp. Radar signals are detected only on 5Ghz range. So this will be detected for 802.11a interface.

bsnAPIfRadarChannelStatisticsEntry.name: bsnAPIfRadarChannelStatisticsEntry
bsnAPIfRadarChannelStatisticsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId, bsnAPIfRadarDetectedCannelNumber.

bsnAPIfRadarDetectedChannelNumber.name: bsnAPIfRadarDetectedChannelNumber
bsnAPIfRadarDetectedChannelNumber.description: Channel Number on which radar signals were detected.

bsnAPIfRadarSignalLastHeard.name: bsnAPIfRadarSignalLastHeard
bsnAPIfRadarSignalLastHeard.description: This tells how many seconds ago radar signal was heard on the channel.

bsnAPIfChannelNoiseInfoTable.name: bsnAPIfChannelNoiseInfoTable
bsnAPIfChannelNoiseInfoTable.description: This is a table of channel information like interference and noise from other 802.11 networks on each channel.

bsnAPIfChannelNoiseInfoEntry.name: bsnAPIfChannelNoiseInfoEntry
bsnAPIfChannelNoiseInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId

bsnAPIfDBNoisePower.name: bsnAPIfDBNoisePower
bsnAPIfDBNoisePower.description: This is the average noise power in dBm on each channel that is available to Airespace AP

bsnAPIfProfileStateTable.name: bsnAPIfProfileStateTable
bsnAPIfProfileStateTable.description: This is a table of state of interference monitor on each Airespace AP

bsnAPIfProfileStateEntry.name: bsnAPIfProfileStateEntry
bsnAPIfProfileStateEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId

bsnAPIfLoadProfileState.name: bsnAPIfLoadProfileState
bsnAPIfLoadProfileState.description: This field represents the current state of the LOAD monitor. This is a total measurement of the business of this Airespace AP. PASS indicates that this Airespace AP is performing adequately compared to the Airespace AP profile. FAIL indicates the Airespace AP is not performing adequately against the LOAD profile.

bsnAPIfInterferenceProfileState.name: bsnAPIfInterferenceProfileState
bsnAPIfInterferenceProfileState.description: This field represents the current state of Interference monitor. This is a total measurement of the interference present at this Airespace AP. PASS indicates that this Airespace AP is performing adequately compared to the Interference profile. FAIL indicates the Airespace AP is not performing adequately against the Interference profile.

bsnAPIfNoiseProfileState.name: bsnAPIfNoiseProfileState
bsnAPIfNoiseProfileState.description: This field represents the current state of Noise monitor. This is a total measurement of the noise present at this Airespace AP. PASS indicates that this Airespace AP is performing adequately compared to the noise profile. FAIL indicates the Airespace AP is not performing adequately against the noise profile.

bsnAPIfCoverageProfileState.name: bsnAPIfCoverageProfileState
bsnAPIfCoverageProfileState.description: This field represents the current state of coverage monitor. This is a total measurement of the client coverage at this Airespace AP. PASS indicates that this Airespace AP is performing adequately compared to the coverage profile. FAIL indicates the Airespace AP is not performing adequately against the coverage profile.

bsnAPIfRxNeighborsTable.name: bsnAPIfRxNeighborsTable
bsnAPIfRxNeighborsTable.description: This is a table of Rx Neighbors for each Airespace AP with their RSSI value.

bsnAPIfRxNeighborsEntry.name: bsnAPIfRxNeighborsEntry
bsnAPIfRxNeighborsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress bsnAPIfSlotId, bsnAPIfRxNeighborMacAddress

bsnAPIfRxNeighborMacAddress.name: bsnAPIfRxNeighborMacAddress
bsnAPIfRxNeighborMacAddress.description: MAC Address of Rx Neighbor of the Airespace AP

bsnAPIfRxNeighborIpAddress.name: bsnAPIfRxNeighborIpAddress
bsnAPIfRxNeighborIpAddress.description: IP Address of Rx Neighbor of the Airespace AP

bsnAPIfRxNeighborRSSI.name: bsnAPIfRxNeighborRSSI
bsnAPIfRxNeighborRSSI.description: RSSI value of the Rx Neighbor

bsnAPIfRxNeighborSlot.name: bsnAPIfRxNeighborSlot
bsnAPIfRxNeighborSlot.description: Slot value of the Rx Neighbor

bsnAPIfRxNeighborChannel.name: bsnAPIfRxNeighborChannel
bsnAPIfRxNeighborChannel.description: This object represents Channel information which neighboring Access point is using.

bsnAPIfRxNeighborChannelWidth.name: bsnAPIfRxNeighborChannelWidth
bsnAPIfRxNeighborChannelWidth.description: This object represents Channel bandwidth information which neighboring Access point is using.

bsnMeshNodeTable.name: bsnMeshNodeTable
bsnMeshNodeTable.description: This is a table of mesh nodes.

bsnMeshNodeEntry.name: bsnMeshNodeEntry
bsnMeshNodeEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress

bsnMeshNodeGroup.name: bsnMeshNodeGroup
bsnMeshNodeGroup.description: the bridge group name of this AP

bsnMeshNodeBackhaul.name: bsnMeshNodeBackhaul
bsnMeshNodeBackhaul.description: the backhaul radio device for this AP

bsnMeshNodeBackhaulRAP.name: bsnMeshNodeBackhaulRAP
bsnMeshNodeBackhaulRAP.description: the backhaul radio device for this AP

bsnMeshNodeMalformedNeighPackets.name: bsnMeshNodeMalformedNeighPackets
bsnMeshNodeMalformedNeighPackets.description: the number of malformed neighbor packets.

bsnMeshNodeBlacklistPackets.name: bsnMeshNodeBlacklistPackets
bsnMeshNodeBlacklistPackets.description: the number of blacklist packets received

bsnMeshNodeEthernetBridge.name: bsnMeshNodeEthernetBridge
bsnMeshNodeEthernetBridge.description: enable : Enables ethernet bridging on the AP. disable : Disables ethernet bridging on the AP. Changes are only applicable when AP is in 'Bridge' mode.

bsnMeshNeighsTable.name: bsnMeshNeighsTable
bsnMeshNeighsTable.description: This is a table of mesh neighbors.

bsnMeshNeighsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress and bsnMeshNeighNeighMacAddress

bsnMeshNeighUnadjustedEase.name: bsnMeshNeighUnadjustedEase
bsnMeshNeighUnadjustedEase.description: ease to root AP from this AP

bsnMeshNeighRapEase.name: bsnMeshNeighRapEase
bsnMeshNeighRapEase.description: unadjusted ease received in last hello

bsnMeshNeighTxParent.name: bsnMeshNeighTxParent
bsnMeshNeighTxParent.description: tx packets to this node while a parent

bsnMeshNeighRxParent.name: bsnMeshNeighRxParent
bsnMeshNeighRxParent.description: rx packets from this node while a parent

bsnMeshNeighPoorSnr.name: bsnMeshNeighPoorSnr
bsnMeshNeighPoorSnr.description: packets with poor snr received from this node

bsnMeshNeighLastUpdate.name: bsnMeshNeighLastUpdate
bsnMeshNeighLastUpdate.description: last received hello from this neighbor

bsnMeshNeighParentChange.name: bsnMeshNeighParentChange
bsnMeshNeighParentChange.description: when this node last became parent

bsnAPIfStationRSSICoverageInfoTable.name: bsnAPIfStationRSSICoverageInfoTable
bsnAPIfStationRSSICoverageInfoTable.description: This is a table of channel information like interference and noise from other 802.11 networks on each channel.

bsnAPIfStationRSSICoverageInfoEntry.name: bsnAPIfStationRSSICoverageInfoEntry
bsnAPIfStationRSSICoverageInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId

bsnAPIfStationCountOnRSSI.name: bsnAPIfStationCountOnRSSI
bsnAPIfStationCountOnRSSI.description: Number of stations on this RSSI Level

bsnAPIfStationSNRCoverageInfoTable.name: bsnAPIfStationSNRCoverageInfoTable
bsnAPIfStationSNRCoverageInfoTable.description: This is a table of Signal to Noise ratio Coverage information on an AP Interface.

bsnAPIfStationSNRCoverageInfoEntry.name: bsnAPIfStationSNRCoverageInfoEntry
bsnAPIfStationSNRCoverageInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId

bsnAPIfStationCountOnSNR.name: bsnAPIfStationCountOnSNR
bsnAPIfStationCountOnSNR.description: Number of stations on this SNR Level

bsnAPIfRecommendedRFParametersTable.name: bsnAPIfRecommendedRFParametersTable
bsnAPIfRecommendedRFParametersTable.description: This table list Best Channel,Best TxPowerLevel, Best RTSThreshold,Best FragmentationThreshold etc for this AP Interface as determined by RRM.

bsnAPIfRecommendedRFParametersEntry.name: bsnAPIfRecommendedRFParametersEntry
bsnAPIfRecommendedRFParametersEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the Table. Entries in this MIB are indexed by bsnAPDot3MacAddress, bsnAPIfSlotId

bsnAPIfRecommendedChannelNumber.name: bsnAPIfRecommendedChannelNumber
bsnAPIfRecommendedChannelNumber.description: Recommended ChannelNumber by RRM for this APIf

bsnAPIfRecommendedTxPowerLevel.name: bsnAPIfRecommendedTxPowerLevel
bsnAPIfRecommendedTxPowerLevel.description: Recommended TxPowerLevel by RRM for this APIf

bsnAPIfRecommendedRTSThreshold.name: bsnAPIfRecommendedRTSThreshold
bsnAPIfRecommendedRTSThreshold.description: Recommended RTSThreshold by RRM for this APIf

bsnAPIfRecommendedFragmentationThreshold.name: bsnAPIfRecommendedFragmentationThreshold
bsnAPIfRecommendedFragmentationThreshold.description: Recommended Fragmentation Threshold by RRM for this APIf

bsnGlobalDot11PrivacyOptionImplemented.name: bsnGlobalDot11PrivacyOptionImplemented
bsnGlobalDot11PrivacyOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the IEEE 802.11 WEP option is implemented. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

bsnGlobalDot11AuthenticationResponseTime.name: bsnGlobalDot11AuthenticationResponseTimeOut
bsnGlobalDot11AuthenticationResponseTime.description: This attribute shall specify the number of TU that a responding STA should wait for the next frame in the authentication sequence.

bsnGlobalDot11MultiDomainCapabilityImple.name: bsnGlobalDot11MultiDomainCapabilityImplemented
bsnGlobalDot11MultiDomainCapabilityImple.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the station implementation is capable of supporting multiple regulatory domains. The capability is disabled, otherwise. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

bsnGlobalDot11MultiDomainCapabilityEnabl.name: bsnGlobalDot11MultiDomainCapabilityEnabled
bsnGlobalDot11MultiDomainCapabilityEnabl.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the capability of the station to operate in multiple regulatory domains is enabled. The capability is disabled, otherwise. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

bsnGlobalDot11CountryIndex.name: bsnGlobalDot11CountryIndex
bsnGlobalDot11CountryIndex.description: This attribute identifies the country in which the station is operating.

bsnGlobalDot11LoadBalancing.name: bsnGlobalDot11LoadBalancing
bsnGlobalDot11LoadBalancing.description: This attribute specifies if load balancing of clients is enabled on disabled. Global configuration of Load Balancing is now removed. Use cLWlanLoadBalancingEnable to configure it per WLAN.

bsnGlobalDot11RogueTimer.name: bsnGlobalDot11RogueTimer
bsnGlobalDot11RogueTimer.description: This attribute specifies in seconds, the time interval after which a Rogue Entry in Rogue Table will expire if no beacon is heard from a Rogue.

bsnPrimaryMwarForAPs.name: bsnPrimaryMwarForAPs
bsnPrimaryMwarForAPs.description: This attribute specifies if this Switch acts a Master Switch for the Airespace APs. So if an Airespace AP doesn't find its Primary Switch, it will associate with this Switch.

bsnSystemCurrentTime.name: bsnSystemCurrentTime
bsnSystemCurrentTime.description: This attribute will display the Current System time on the Switch.

bsnUpdateSystemTime.name: bsnUpdateSystemTime
bsnUpdateSystemTime.description: Use this attribute to change the System time on the Switch. Specify the new time in this Format MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS

bsnOperatingTemperatureEnvironment.name: bsnOperatingTemperatureEnvironment
bsnOperatingTemperatureEnvironment.description: Operating Environment of the Airespace Switch. commercial is Commercial (0 to 40 C) and industrial is Industrial (-10 to 70 C)

bsnSensorTemperature.name: bsnSensorTemperature
bsnSensorTemperature.description: Current Internal Temperature of the unit in Centigrade

bsnTemperatureAlarmLowLimit.name: bsnTemperatureAlarmLowLimit
bsnTemperatureAlarmLowLimit.description: Internal Temperature Alarm Low Limit in Centigrade. If the bsnSensorTemperature goes below this limit bsnSensedTemperatureTooLow Alarm will be sent out

bsnTemperatureAlarmHighLimit.name: bsnTemperatureAlarmHighLimit
bsnTemperatureAlarmHighLimit.description: Internal Temperature Alarm High Limit in Centigrade. If the bsnSensorTemperature goes above this limit bsnSensedTemperatureTooHigh Alarm will be sent out

bsnVirtualGatewayAddress.name: bsnVirtualGatewayAddress
bsnVirtualGatewayAddress.description: Virtual Gateway Address of the Switch. This is used by web auth and Ipsec. If the virtual IP Address is changed, the Switch has to be rebooted for the new Address to take effect. This is now replaced by the Virtual Interface in bsnswitching MIB.

bsnRFMobilityDomainName.name: bsnRFMobilityDomainName
bsnRFMobilityDomainName.description: RF Mobility Group Name to which this Airespace Switch belongs. Airespace Switches on a network form a RF Group as well as a Mobility Group. RF Groups does the channel and power management of AP while Mobility Group does load balancing and hand off for clients.

bsnClientWatchListFeature.name: bsnClientWatchListFeature
bsnClientWatchListFeature.description: This flag should be turned on for the client watch lists to be enabled on the switch. When enabled, the switch generates Client Association and Authentication traps for the watchlisted clients.

bsnRogueLocationDiscoveryProtocol.name: bsnRogueLocationDiscoveryProtocol
bsnRogueLocationDiscoveryProtocol.description: This flag should be turned on to enable the Rogue Location Discovery Protocol feature on the switch. We can either enable this feature for all the APs or only for APs in monitor mode.

bsnRogueAutoContainFeature.name: bsnRogueAutoContainFeature
bsnRogueAutoContainFeature.description: This flag should be turned on to allow the switch to contain the rogues automatically if detected on the wired network.

bsnOverAirProvisionApMode.name: bsnOverAirProvisionApMode
bsnOverAirProvisionApMode.description: Over the Air Provisioning Mode for APs

bsnMaximumNumberOfConcurrentLogins.name: bsnMaximumNumberOfConcurrentLogins
bsnMaximumNumberOfConcurrentLogins.description: This attribute specifies the maximum number of concurrent logins that the switch will allow for a single user. A value 0 implies that there is no restriction on the number of concurrent logins with a single username.

bsnAutoContainRoguesAdvertisingSsid.name: bsnAutoContainRoguesAdvertisingSsid
bsnAutoContainRoguesAdvertisingSsid.description: This flag should be set to 1 to allow the switch to contain automatically those rogues that are advertising our SSID. If value is 0, only an alarm will be generated when such a rogue is detected.

bsnAutoContainAdhocNetworks.name: bsnAutoContainAdhocNetworks
bsnAutoContainAdhocNetworks.description: This flag should be set to 1 to allow the switch to contain automatically the adhoc networks detected by the switch. If value is 0, only an alarm will be generated when such a network is detected.

bsnAutoContainTrustedClientsOnRogueAps.name: bsnAutoContainTrustedClientsOnRogueAps
bsnAutoContainTrustedClientsOnRogueAps.description: This flag should be set to 1 to allow the switch to contain automatically those trusted clients that are associated to rogue APs. If value is 0, only an alarm will be generated when such a client is detected.

bsnValidateRogueClientsAgainstAAA.name: bsnValidateRogueClientsAgainstAAA
bsnValidateRogueClientsAgainstAAA.description: This flag should be turned on to allow the switch to validate 'valid' mobiles associating with rogue APs. For example, if a client's MAC Address is found in the local MAC filter table, that client can be validated.

bsnSystemTimezoneDelta.name: bsnSystemTimezoneDelta
bsnSystemTimezoneDelta.description: The delta (difference) between the local time and the Universal Coordinated Time in hours. For example, it is -8 for the PST and +1 for France. If the delta is -5.30 then this attribute will store -5 and bsnSystemTimezoneDeltaMinutes will store 30. This value i should be between -23 to +23

bsnSystemTimezoneDeltaMinutes.name: bsnSystemTimezoneDeltaMinutes
bsnSystemTimezoneDeltaMinutes.description: The minutes component of delta (difference) between the local time and the Universal Coordinated Time.

bsnSystemTimezoneDaylightSavings.name: bsnSystemTimezoneDaylightSavings
bsnSystemTimezoneDaylightSavings.description: This flag specifies if daylight savings are enabled for the current timezone.

bsnAllowAuthorizeApAgainstAAA.name: bsnAllowAuthorizeApAgainstAAA
bsnAllowAuthorizeApAgainstAAA.description: This flag specifies if LWAPP is allowed to get authorization via RADIUS or local database for an AP.

bsnApFallbackEnabled.name: bsnApFallbackEnabled
bsnApFallbackEnabled.description: This flag specifies if the APs should continue LWAPP discoveries to fallback to the primary switch in case they are not already associated with it i.e they are associated with their respective secondary or tertiary switch instead.

bsnAppleTalkEnabled.name: bsnAppleTalkEnabled
bsnAppleTalkEnabled.description: This flag turns on the appletalk bridging in the switch such that the packets from Apple clients that use appletalk format can be processed by the switch. When this flag is off, these packets are dropped.

bsnPolicyForMisconfiguredAps.name: bsnPolicyForMisconfiguredAps
bsnPolicyForMisconfiguredAps.description: This flag should be turned on to allow the switch to contain misconfigured APs.

bsnEncryptionPolicyEnforced.name: bsnEncryptionPolicyEnforced
bsnEncryptionPolicyEnforced.description: The encryption policy that is enforced on the trusted APs.

bsnPreamblePolicyEnforced.name: bsnPreamblePolicyEnforced
bsnPreamblePolicyEnforced.description: The preamble policy that is enforced on the trusted APs.

bsnDot11ModePolicyEnforced.name: bsnDot11ModePolicyEnforced
bsnDot11ModePolicyEnforced.description: The 802.11 Mode policy that is enforced on the trusted APs.

bsnRadioTypePolicyEnforced.name: bsnRadioTypePolicyEnforced
bsnRadioTypePolicyEnforced.description: The radio type policy that is enforced on the trusted APs.

bsnValidateSsidForTrustedAp.name: bsnValidateSsidForTrustedAp
bsnValidateSsidForTrustedAp.description: If enabled, the SSID of trusted APs will be validated by the switch.

bsnAlertIfTrustedApMissing.name: bsnAlertIfTrustedApMissing
bsnAlertIfTrustedApMissing.description: If enabled, an alert will be generated when a trusted AP is missing.

bsnTrustedApEntryExpirationTimeout.name: bsnTrustedApEntryExpirationTimeout
bsnTrustedApEntryExpirationTimeout.description: This attribute specifies in seconds, the time interval after which a Trusted AP Entry will expire if no beacon is heard from that AP.

bsnExcessive80211AssocFailures.name: bsnExcessive80211AssocFailures
bsnExcessive80211AssocFailures.description: This flag specifies if client should be excluded (blacklisted) if repeated 802.11 Association Failures occurs with a client.

bsnExcessive80211AuthFailures.name: bsnExcessive80211AuthFailures
bsnExcessive80211AuthFailures.description: This flag specifies if client should be excluded (blacklisted) if repeated 802.11 Authentication Failures occurs with a client.

bsnExcessive8021xAuthFailures.name: bsnExcessive8021xAuthFailures
bsnExcessive8021xAuthFailures.description: This flag specifies if client should be excluded (blacklisted) if repeated 802.1x Authentication Failures occurs with a client.

bsnExternalPolicyServerFailures.name: bsnExternalPolicyServerFailures
bsnExternalPolicyServerFailures.description: This flag specifies if client should be excluded (blacklisted) if repeated external policy server failures occurs with a client.

bsnExcessiveWebAuthFailures.name: bsnExcessiveWebAuthFailures
bsnExcessiveWebAuthFailures.description: This flag specifies if client should be excluded (blacklisted) if repeated Web Authentication Failures occurs with a client.

bsnIPTheftORReuse.name: bsnIPTheftORReuse
bsnIPTheftORReuse.description: This flag specifies if client should be excluded (blacklisted) if it appears to be reusing an IP Address.(Possible IP Theft)

bsnStandardSignatureTable.name: bsnStandardSignatureTable
bsnStandardSignatureTable.description: The table listing Standard Signatures configured on the switch. The standard signatures are provided with the released product. The standard signatures can be updated via file download to the switch. The table is indexed by the precedence of the signatures.

bsnStandardSignaturePrecedence.name: bsnStandardSignaturePrecedence
bsnStandardSignaturePrecedence.description: Precedence of the signature. This specifies the order in which the signature is applied to a packet.

bsnStandardSignatureName.name: bsnStandardSignatureName
bsnStandardSignatureName.description: This attribute is used to configure the name on a signature.

bsnStandardSignatureDescription.name: bsnStandardSignatureDescription
bsnStandardSignatureDescription.description: This attribute is used to configure the description of a signature.

bsnStandardSignatureFrameType.name: bsnStandardSignatureFrameType
bsnStandardSignatureFrameType.description: This attribute specifies the type of frame that needs to match a signature.

bsnStandardSignatureAction.name: bsnStandardSignatureAction
bsnStandardSignatureAction.description: This attribute specifies the action to be taken once a packet is found to match a signature.

bsnStandardSignatureState.name: bsnStandardSignatureState
bsnStandardSignatureState.description: This attribute specifies the state of a signature. It is used to match packets only if the state is enabled.

bsnStandardSignatureFrequency.name: bsnStandardSignatureFrequency
bsnStandardSignatureFrequency.description: This specifies the frequency of the matching packets after which the specified action is taken.

bsnStandardSignatureQuietTime.name: bsnStandardSignatureQuietTime
bsnStandardSignatureQuietTime.description: This specifies the quiet time in seconds during which no matching packets are found after which the attack is considered stopped.

bsnStandardSignatureConfigType.name: bsnStandardSignatureConfigType
bsnStandardSignatureConfigType.description: This attribute specifies the type of Signature configuration. It's protocol when the protocol format is used in the UI to configure this. Pattern is the config type for all signatures in the released signature file and when signatures are configured using pattern format. Note: the signatures will be allowed to be i configured in later releases.

bsnStandardSignatureEnable.name: bsnStandardSignatureEnable
bsnStandardSignatureEnable.description: This object configures the status of a particular standard signature on LWAPP APs, for use in performing signature analysis on the received 802.11 data and/or management frames. A value of 'true' makes the Controller send the 'Signature Add LWAPP Message' to all the joined APs with the status field set to 'enable'. This makes the joined APs perform signature analysis on the received 802.11 data and/or management frames and report the discrepancies observed, if any, to the Controller. A value of 'false' makes the Controller send the 'Signature Add LWAPP Message' to all the joined APs with the status field set to 'disable'. The joined APs doesn't perform the signature analysis on the received 802.11 data and/or management frames for this particular signature, till the signature is enabled.

bsnStandardSignatureMacInfo.name: bsnStandardSignatureMacInfo
bsnStandardSignatureMacInfo.description: This object defines the pattern followed by the LWAPP APs to perform signature analysis with this Standard signature and report the results to the Controller.

bsnStandardSignatureMacFreq.name: bsnStandardSignatureMacFreq
bsnStandardSignatureMacFreq.description: This object specifies the frequency of matching packets from a particular source after which the specified action is taken.

bsnStandardSignatureRowStatus.name: bsnStandardSignatureRowStatus
bsnStandardSignatureRowStatus.description: Row Status for creation/deletion. Signature will allowed to be created, deleted and edited in later releases.

bsnStandardSignatureInterval.name: bsnStandardSignatureInterval
bsnStandardSignatureInterval.description: Interval of the signature. This specifies the interval when the signature is applied to a packet.

bsnStandardSignaturePatternTable.name: bsnStandardSignaturePatternTable
bsnStandardSignaturePatternTable.description: The table listing the matching patterns specified for a i Standard Signature. These are instrumental in matching the signature with a packet. A maximum of 5 i patterns may be specifed for a signature. These are used for matching in the order of their index.

bsnStandardSignaturePatternIndex.name: bsnStandardSignaturePatternIndex
bsnStandardSignaturePatternIndex.description: Index of the pattern. This specifies the order in which the pattern is checked against the packet contents.

bsnStandardSignaturePatternOffset.name: bsnStandardSignaturePatternOffset
bsnStandardSignaturePatternOffset.description: Offset from the start of the packet where the AP looks for a match to the pattern.

bsnStandardSignaturePatternString.name: bsnStandardSignaturePatternString
bsnStandardSignaturePatternString.description: This is the pattern string that the AP uses to match at the offset. Example: 0x616c7068615f3178

bsnStandardSignaturePatternMask.name: bsnStandardSignaturePatternMask
bsnStandardSignaturePatternMask.description: This is the pattern mask. This is the bit mask that the AP uses to mask out the bits in the packet at the given offset. Example: 0xffffffffffffffff

bsnStandardSignaturePatternOffSetStart.name: bsnStandardSignaturePatternOffSetStart
bsnStandardSignaturePatternOffSetStart.description: This object indicates how an offset should be applied while doing signature analysis for QOS and non-QOS data frames with this standard signature.

bsnStandardSignaturePatternRowStatus.name: bsnStandardSignaturePatternRowStatus
bsnStandardSignaturePatternRowStatus.description: Row Status for creation/deletion. Signature Pattern will allowed to be created, deleted and edited in later releases.

bsnRfIdTagAutoTimeoutStatus.name: bsnRfIdTagAutoTimeoutStatus

bsnGlobalDot11bRTSThreshold.name: bsnGlobalDot11bRTSThreshold
bsnGlobalDot11bRTSThreshold.description: This attribute shall indicate the number of octets in an MPDU, below which an RTS/CTS handshake shall not be performed. An RTS/CTS handshake shall be performed at the beginning of any frame exchange sequence where the MPDU is of type Data or Management, the MPDU has an individual address in the Address1 field, and the length of the MPDU is greater than this threshold. (For additional details, refer to Table 21 in 9.7.) Setting this attribute to be larger than the maximum MSDU size shall have the effect of turning off the RTS/CTS handshake for frames of Data or Management type transmitted by this STA. Setting this attribute to zero shall have the effect of turning on the RTS/CTS handshake for all frames of Data or Management type transmitted by this STA. The default value of this attribute shall be 2347.

bsnGlobalDot11bShortRetryLimit.name: bsnGlobalDot11bShortRetryLimit

The default value of this attribute shall be 7.

bsnGlobalDot11bLongRetryLimit.name: bsnGlobalDot11bLongRetryLimit
bsnGlobalDot11bLongRetryLimit.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is greater than bsnGlobalDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated. The default value of this attribute shall be 4.

bsnGlobalDot11bFragmentationThreshold.name: bsnGlobalDot11bFragmentationThreshold

The default value for this attribute shall be the lesser of 2346 or the aMPDUMaxLength of the attached PHY and shall never exceed the lesser of 2346 or the aMPDUMaxLength of the attached PHY. The value of this attribute shall never be less than 256.

bsnGlobalDot11bMaxTransmitMSDULifetime.description: The MaxTransmitMSDULifetime shall be the elapsed time in TU, after the initial transmission of an MSDU, after which further attempts to transmit the MSDU shall be terminated. The default value of this attribute shall be 512.

Setting this attribute to zero shall have the effect of turning on the RTS/CTS handshake for all frames of Data or Management type transmitted by this STA. The default value of this attribute shall be 2347.

bsnGlobalDot11aShortRetryLimit.name: bsnGlobalDot11aShortRetryLimit
bsnGlobalDot11aShortRetryLimit.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to bsnGlobalDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated. The default value of this attribute shall be 7.

bsnGlobalDot11aLongRetryLimit.name: bsnGlobalDot11aLongRetryLimit
bsnGlobalDot11aLongRetryLimit.description: This attribute shall indicate the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is greater than bsnGlobalDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated. The default value of this attribute shall be 4.

bsnGlobalDot11aFragmentationThreshold.name: bsnGlobalDot11aFragmentationThreshold
bsnGlobalDot11aFragmentationThreshold.description: This attribute shall specify the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. An MSDU shall be broken into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers. MSDU or MMPDU shall be fragmented when the resulting frame has an individual address in the Address1 field, and the length of the frame is larger than this threshold. The default value for this attribute shall be the lesser of 2346 or the aMPDUMaxLength of the attached PHY and shall never exceed the lesser of 2346 or the aMPDUMaxLength of the attached PHY. The value of this attribute shall never be less than 256.

bsnGlobalDot11aMaxTransmitMSDULifetime.name: bsnGlobalDot11aMaxTransmitMSDULifetime
bsnGlobalDot11aMaxTransmitMSDULifetime.description: The MaxTransmitMSDULifetime shall be the elapsed time in TU, after the initial transmission of an MSDU, after which further attempts to transmit the MSDU shall be terminated. The default value of this attribute shall be 512.

bsnGlobalDot11aMaxReceiveLifetime.name: bsnGlobalDot11aMaxReceiveLifetime
bsnGlobalDot11aMaxReceiveLifetime.description: The MaxReceiveLifetime shall be the elapsed time in TU, after the initial reception of a fragmented MMPDU or MSDU, after which further attempts to reassemble the MMPDU or MSDU shall be terminated. The default value shall be 512.

bsnGlobalDot11aTIThreshold.name: bsnGlobalDot11aTIThreshold
bsnGlobalDot11aTIThreshold.description: The Threshold being used to detect a busy medium (frequency). CCA shall report a busy medium upon detecting the RSSI above this threshold.

bsnGlobalDot11aChannelAgilityEnabled.name: bsnGlobalDot11aChannelAgilityEnabled
bsnGlobalDot11aChannelAgilityEnabled.description: This attribute indicates that the PHY channel agility functionality is enabled.

bsnGlobalDot11hPowerConstraint.name: bsnGlobalDot11hPowerConstraint
bsnGlobalDot11hPowerConstraint.description: Local maximum transmit power for a channel is defined as maximum transmit power level specified for the channel in the Country element minus the local power constraint specified for the channel in the Power Constraint element.The power constraint is coded as an unsigned integer in units of decibels. To disable power constraint set Power Constraint to 0.

bsnGlobalDot11hChannelSwitchEnable.name: bsnGlobalDot11hChannelSwitchEnable

bsnGlobalDot11hChannelSwitchMode.name: bsnGlobalDot11hChannelSwitchMode
bsnGlobalDot11hChannelSwitchMode.description: The Channel Switch Mode indicates any restriction on transmission until a channel switch. An Channel mode set to 1 means that the STA in a BSS to which the frame containing the element is addressed shall tranmit no further frames with in the BSS until the scheduled channel switch. A Channel switch mode set to 0 does not impose any requirement on the receiving STA.

If the key is present in request, it should be taken as a hint by the server that the sender prefers this method of encryption over others. To maintain security actual keys after configuration are never returned in get request. If keys are configured then '***' is returned. If keys are not configured then empty string is retunred. bsnRadiusAuthServerKeyFormat is used this key. if the format chosen is ascii then it should be 16 bytes in length. if the format chosen is hex then it should be 32 bytes in length.

bsnRadiusAuthServerKeyWrapMACKkey.name: bsnRadiusAuthServerKeyWrapMACKkey
bsnRadiusAuthServerKeyWrapMACKkey.description: Message-authenticator-code-key ( MACK) - used as the key for the HMAC-SHA-1 algorithm to sign the RADIUS message to prevent spoofing. MACK must be configured when KEK is configured. To maintain security actual keys after configuration are never returned in get request. If keys are configured then '***' is returned. If keys are not configured then empty string is returned. bsnRadiusAuthServerKeyFormat is used this key. if the format chosen is ascii then it should be 20 bytes in length. If the format chosen is hex then it should be 40 bytes in length.

bsnRadiusAuthServerKeyWrapFormat.description: Format for the Key Wrap keys. This object is mandatory for manager to send if the key Wrap keys are being configured. Get on this object will always return hex(1)

bsnMacFilterTable.name: bsnMacFilterTable
bsnMacFilterTable.description: The table listing MAC Filter entries

bsnMacFilterWlanId.name: bsnMacFilterWlanId
bsnMacFilterWlanId.description: WLAN ID of the WLAN that the user can connect to. 0 means any WLAN ID.

bsnMacFilterDescription.name: bsnMacFilterDescription
bsnMacFilterDescription.description: Description of the MAC Filter entry.

bsnLocalNetUserTable.name: bsnLocalNetUserTable
bsnLocalNetUserTable.description: The table listing Local Net User entries.

bsnLocalNetUserWlanId.name: bsnLocalNetUserWlanId
bsnLocalNetUserWlanId.description: WLAN ID of the WLAN that the user can connect to. 0 means any WLAN ID.

bsnLocalNetUserDescription.name: bsnLocalNetUserDescription
bsnLocalNetUserDescription.description: Description of the Net User entry.

bsnLocalNetUserLifetime.name: bsnLocalNetUserLifetime
bsnLocalNetUserLifetime.description: This object indicates the lifetime of an user account expressed in hundredths of a second. Lifetime period other than 0 will make it a guest-user. Minimum value for guest user is 60 seconds (6000). Once configured as non-guest user can not be change to guest user and vice-versa. Default value is for a day and max lifetime is 259200000(30 days). WLANIds, which have webauth policy are valid for guest access user.

bsnLocalNetUserStartTime.name: bsnLocalNetUserStartTime
bsnLocalNetUserStartTime.description: This object indicates the time when the guest user account was created and expressed as the number of seconds elapsed since 1st Jan, 1970.

bsnLocalNetUserRemainingTime.name: bsnLocalNetUserRemainingTime
bsnLocalNetUserRemainingTime.description: This object indicates the remaining session time for the guest user in hundredths of a second.

bsnLocalManagementUserTable.name: bsnLocalManagementUserTable
bsnLocalManagementUserTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing Local Management Users

bsnAclTable.name: bsnAclTable
bsnAclTable.description: The table listing ACLs (Access Control Lists) on the Switch.

bsnAclName.name: bsnAclName
bsnAclName.description: Name of the Access Control List.

bsnAclApplyMode.name: bsnAclApplyMode
bsnAclApplyMode.description: The apply mode of the ACL on the switch. Mode value 'applied' means the ACL has been applied on the switch.

bsnAclRuleTable.name: bsnAclRuleTable
bsnAclRuleTable.description: The table listing Acl Rules(Access Control List Entries) on the ACL with name bsnAclName.

bsnAclRuleIndex.name: bsnAclRuleIndex
bsnAclRuleIndex.description: Index of the ACL rule. This can be updated to reset the sequence of the rules of an ACL.

bsnAclRuleAction.name: bsnAclRuleAction
bsnAclRuleAction.description: The permission mode of a rule.

bsnAclRuleDirection.name: bsnAclRuleDirection
bsnAclRuleDirection.description: The direction of the packet to which the rule may be applied.

bsnAclRuleSourceIpAddress.name: bsnAclRuleSourceIpAddress
bsnAclRuleSourceIpAddress.description: Source IP Address of the ACL rule. A value 0 implies any source address.

bsnAclRuleSourceIpNetmask.name: bsnAclRuleSourceIpNetmask
bsnAclRuleSourceIpNetmask.description: Source IP Netmask of the ACL rule. A value 0 implies any source mask.

bsnAclRuleDestinationIpAddress.name: bsnAclRuleDestinationIpAddress
bsnAclRuleDestinationIpAddress.description: Destination IP Address of the ACL rule. A value 0 implies any destination address.

bsnAclRuleDestinationIpNetmask.name: bsnAclRuleDestinationIpNetmask
bsnAclRuleDestinationIpNetmask.description: Destination Netmask of the ACL rule. A value 0 implies any destination mask.

bsnAclRuleProtocol.name: bsnAclRuleProtocol
bsnAclRuleProtocol.description: Protocol of the packet. It can be either of the pre specified protocols like TCP, UDP, ICMP, ESP, AH, GRE, IP, Ethernet Over IP, OSPF or any number between 0 and 255. A value 256 implies that this rule applies to 'Any' protocol.

bsnAclRuleStartSourcePort.name: bsnAclRuleStartSourcePort
bsnAclRuleStartSourcePort.description: Source Port of the packet. It can be either of the pre specified ports like HTTP, HTTPS, Telnet, RADIUS etc or any number between 0 and 65535. A value 65536 implies that this rule applies to 'Any' source port. This value can be set only if the protocol is set to TCP or UDP. Otherwise the value is set to Any(65536)

bsnAclRuleEndSourcePort.name: bsnAclRuleEndSourcePort
bsnAclRuleEndSourcePort.description: Source Port of the packet. It can be either of the pre specified ports like HTTP, HTTPS, Telnet, RADIUS etc or any number between 0 and 65535. A value 65536 implies that this rule applies to 'Any' source port. This value can be set only if the protocol is set to TCP or UDP. Otherwise the value is set to Any(65536)

bsnAclRuleStartDestinationPort.name: bsnAclRuleStartDestinationPort
bsnAclRuleStartDestinationPort.description: Destination Port of the packet. It can be either of the pre specified ports like HTTP, HTTPS, Telnet, RADIUS etc or any number between 0 and 65535. A value 65536 implies that this rule aplpies to 'Any' Destination port. This value can be set only if the protocol is set to TCP or UDP. Otherwise the value is set to Any(65536)

bsnAclRuleEndDestinationPort.name: bsnAclRuleEndDestinationPort
bsnAclRuleEndDestinationPort.description: Destination Port of the packet. It can be either of the pre specified ports like HTTP, HTTPS, Telnet, RADIUS etc or any number between 0 and 65535. A value 65536 implies that this rule aplpies to 'Any' Destination port. This value can be set only if the protocol is set to TCP or UDP. Otherwise the value is set to Any(65536)

bsnAclRuleDscp.name: bsnAclRuleDscp
bsnAclRuleDscp.description: DSCP value of the rule. A value 256 implies Any

bsnAclNewRuleIndex.name: bsnAclNewRuleIndex
bsnAclNewRuleIndex.description: New Index of the ACL rule. This attribute should be updated if the requirement is to reset the sequence of the rules of an ACL. A read on this will not yield anything.

bsnAclRuleRowStatus.name: bsnAclRuleRowStatus
bsnAclRuleRowStatus.description: Row Status of the ACL Rule.

bsnRadiusAuthKeyWrapEnable.name: bsnRadiusAuthKeyWrapEnable
bsnRadiusAuthKeyWrapEnable.description: When keyWrap is enable then for 801.1X and 802.11i client Authentication, request is sent to those radius servers which has KEK and MACK keys are configured. Radius servers are widely used for user authentications. In 802.11i and 802.1X type authentication, the controller recives Pairwise Master KEy(PMK) from RADIUS sever using vendor specific RADIUS attributes, which uses MPPE RFC3078. Since MPPE uses RC4 algorithm to provide data confidentiality, it is not FIPS approved. For this RADIUS key WRAP attributes, bsnRadiusAuthServerKeyWrap and bsnRadiusAuthServerKeyWrapMACKkey have been added, which are used to securely transfer encryption keys using non-proprietary techniques.

bsnRadiusAuthCacheCredentialsLocally.name: bsnRadiusAuthCacheCredentialsLocally
bsnRadiusAuthCacheCredentialsLocally.description: Enable or disable caching of credentials locally for RADIUS Auth servers. This is used when a client uses a one time password authentication scheme.

bsnAAAMacDelimiter.name: bsnAAAMacDelimiter
bsnAAAMacDelimiter.description: The delimiter to be used for mac filtering. It can be colon as in xx:xx:xx:xx:xx:xx or hyphen as in xx-xx-xx-xx-xx-xx or single hyphen as in xxxxxx-xxxxxx or no delimiter as in xxxxxxxxxxxx.

bsnAAARadiusCompatibilityMode.name: bsnAAARadiusCompatibilityMode
bsnAAARadiusCompatibilityMode.description: The required compatibility mode for MAC filtering. For ciscoACS, the expected MAC delimiter setting is colon and for orinocoRadius, it is singleHyphen.

bsnAAARadiusCallStationIdType.name: bsnAAARadiusCallStationIdType
bsnAAARadiusCallStationIdType.description: This attribute configures the call station ID information sent in RADIUS messages. The value undefined cannot be set during the write operation.

bsnAAALocalDatabaseSize.name: bsnAAALocalDatabaseSize
bsnAAALocalDatabaseSize.description: This attribute is the total number of entries permitted in the local users database. This is the combined total of entries for Local Management Users, Local Net Users, Disabled Clients (previously known as blacklistclients and the MAC Filters. If the database size limit is reached, no more entries in any of these user lists are allowed to be created. To continue creating more entries, one should increase the size of the database. This value is applied on reboot and then matches the bsnAACurrentLocalDatabaseSize.

bsnAAACurrentLocalDatabaseSize.name: bsnAAACurrentLocalDatabaseSize
bsnAAACurrentLocalDatabaseSize.description: This attribute is the maximum number of entries in the local users database that is effective currently. This is the combined total of entries for Local Management Users, Local Net Users, Disabled Clients (previously known as blacklist clients) and the MAC Filters.

bsnBlackListClientTable.name: bsnBlackListClientTable
bsnBlackListClientTable.description: The table listing Wlan Black Listed Clients

bsnExternalPolicyServerTable.name: bsnExternalPolicyServerTable
bsnExternalPolicyServerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the External Policy servers with which client share a secret.

bsnExternalPolicyServerEntry.name: bsnExternalPolicyServerEntry
bsnExternalPolicyServerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an External policy server with which the client shares a secret.

bsnExternalPolicyServerIndex.name: bsnExternalPolicyServerIndex
bsnExternalPolicyServerIndex.description: A number uniquely identifying each External Policy server with which this client communicates.

bsnExternalPolicyServerAddress.name: bsnExternalPolicyServerAddress
bsnExternalPolicyServerAddress.description: The IP address of the External Policy server referred to in this table entry.

bsnExternalPolicyServerPortNumber.name: bsnExternalPolicyServerPortNumber
bsnExternalPolicyServerPortNumber.description: The UDP port the client is using to send requests to this server.

bsnExternalPolicyServerKey.name: bsnExternalPolicyServerKey
bsnExternalPolicyServerKey.description: The authentication and encryption key shared between the client and this External Policy Server.

bsnExternalPolicyServerAclName.name: bsnExternalPolicyServerAclName
bsnExternalPolicyServerAclName.description: This attribute configures the ACL Name for External Policy Servers

bsnAcceptSelfSignedCertificate.name: bsnAcceptSelfSignedCertificate
bsnAcceptSelfSignedCertificate.description: This flag specifies if controller will accept Self Signed Certificate from AP as part of authorization.

bsnSystemClockTime.name: bsnSystemClockTime
bsnSystemClockTime.description: This object represents the current clock time of the controller and expressed as the number of seconds elapsed since 00:00:00 on January 1, 1970, Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

bsnAPAuthorizationTable.name: bsnAPAuthorizationTable
bsnAPAuthorizationTable.description: The table listing AP Authorization entries

bsnAPAuthMacAddress.name: bsnAPAuthMacAddress
bsnAPAuthMacAddress.description: MAC Address of the AP entry

bsnAPAuthCertificateType.name: bsnAPAuthCertificateType
bsnAPAuthCertificateType.description: Supported certificate types are MIC, SSC (Self-Signed-Certificate) or no certificate.

bsnAPAuthHashKey.name: bsnAPAuthHashKey
bsnAPAuthHashKey.description: SHA1 hash key for SSC certificate validation. It has to be 40/64 hexa-decimal characters. This is considered when certificate type is SSC.

bsnWrasIpsecCACertificateUpdate.name: bsnWrasIpsecCACertificateUpdate
bsnWrasIpsecCACertificateUpdate.description: Note this attribute is for updating the certificate If you try to read it, it will always be ***

bsnWrasIpsecCertEntry.name: bsnWrasIpsecCertEntry
bsnWrasIpsecCertEntry.description: Each entry contains a specific certificate.

bsnWrasIpsecCertName.name: bsnWrasIpsecCertName
bsnWrasIpsecCertName.description: The name assigned to this set of IKE Certificates.

bsnWrasIpsecCertificateUpdate.name: bsnWrasIpsecCertificateUpdate
bsnWrasIpsecCertificateUpdate.description: If you try to read this it will always be ***

bsnWrasIpsecCertStatus.name: bsnWrasIpsecCertStatus
bsnWrasIpsecCertStatus.description: A row status type for the IKE Cert Entry.

bsnDot11StationTrapControlMask.name: bsnDot11StationTrapControlMask
bsnDot11StationTrapControlMask.description: This mask describes what events merit traps to network management. If the bit for a particular event is turned on then notification will be generated on event occurence. Event corresponding value ----- ----------------- bsnDot11StationDisassociate 1 bsnDot11StationDeauthenticate 2 bsnDot11StationAuthenticateFail 4 bsnDot11StationAssociateFail 8 bsnDot11StationBlacklisted 16 bsnDot11StationAssociate 32 ciscoLwappDot11ClientMovedToRunState 64 By Default all bits are off.

bsnDot11StationDisassociate.name: bsnDot11StationDisassociate
bsnDot11StationDisassociate.description: The disassociate notification shall be sent when the Station sends a Disassociation frame. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the MAC to which the Disassociation frame was sent and the reason for the disassociation

bsnDot11StationDeauthenticate.name: bsnDot11StationDeauthenticate
bsnDot11StationDeauthenticate.description: The deauthenticate notification shall be sent when the Station sends a Deauthentication frame. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the MAC to which the Deauthentication frame was sent and the reason for the deauthentication.

bsnDot11StationAuthenticateFail.name: bsnDot11StationAuthenticateFail
bsnDot11StationAuthenticateFail.description: The authenticate failure notification shall be sent when the Station sends an Authentication frame with a status code other than 'successful'. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the MAC to which the Authentication frame was sent and the reason for the authentication failure.

bsnDot11StationAssociateFail.name: bsnDot11StationAssociateFail
bsnDot11StationAssociateFail.description: The associate failure notification shall be sent when the Station sends an Association frame with a status code other than 'successful'. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the MAC to which the Authentication frame was sent and the reason for the authentication failure.

bsnDot11StationBlacklisted.name: bsnDot11StationBlacklisted
bsnDot11StationBlacklisted.description: The station blacklisted notification shall be sent when the client is blacklisted. The reason could be repeated auth or association failures or IP Address theft. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the MAC to which the Authentication frame was sent, the MAC and Slot Id of AP that client was associated to and the reason for black listing.

bsnDot11StationAssociate.name: bsnDot11StationAssociate
bsnDot11StationAssociate.description: The associate notification shall be sent when any of the watchlisted clients(present on at least one watch list) associates with an AP. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address and the Slot ID of the radio to which the station Associated.

bsnAPTrapControlMask.name: bsnAPTrapControlMask
bsnAPTrapControlMask.description: This mask describes what events merit traps to network management. If the bit for a particular event is turned on then notification will be generated on event occurance. Event corresponding bit ----- ----------------- bsnAPAssociate/Disassociate 1 bsnAPIfUp/Down 4 bsnAPAuthorizationFailureCause 16 bsnAPModeChanged 32 bsnAPTimeSyncFailure 64 By Default all bits are on.

bsnAPUp.name: bsnAPUp
bsnAPUp.description: When Airespace AP operation status goes up this trap will be sent

bsnAPDown.name: bsnAPDown
bsnAPDown.description: When Airespace AP operation status goes down this trap will be sent

bsnAPAssociated.name: bsnAPAssociated
bsnAPAssociated.description: When Airespace AP Associates to a Airespace Switch, AP associated notification will be sent with dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP.This will help management system to discover Airespace AP and add to system.

bsnAPDisassociated.name: bsnAPDisassociated
bsnAPDisassociated.description: When Airespace AP disassociates from Airespace Switch, AP disassociated notification will be sent with dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP management system to remove Airespace AP from this Airespace Switch

bsnAPIfUp.name: bsnAPIfUp
bsnAPIfUp.description: When Airespace AP's interface's operation status goes up this trap will be sent

bsnAPIfDown.name: bsnAPIfDown
bsnAPIfDown.description: When Airespace AP's interface's operation status goes down this trap will be sent.

bsnAPProfileTrapControlMask.name: bsnAPProfileTrapControlMask
bsnAPProfileTrapControlMask.description: This mask describes what events merit traps to network management. If the bit for a particular event is turned on then notification will be generated on event occurance. Event corresponding bit ----- ----------------- LoadProfileFail 1 NoiseProfileFail 2 InterferenceProfileFail 4 CoverageProfileFailed 8

bsnAPLoadProfileFailed.name: bsnAPLoadProfileFailed
bsnAPLoadProfileFailed.description: When LOAD Profile state changes from PASS to FAIL, notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF. This trap sending can be enable/disable using bsnRrmProfileTrapControlFlag

bsnAPNoiseProfileFailed.name: bsnAPNoiseProfileFailed
bsnAPNoiseProfileFailed.description: When Noise Profile state changes from PASS to FAIL, notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF. This trap sending can be enable/disable using bsnRrmProfileTrapControlFlag

bsnAPInterferenceProfileFailed.name: bsnAPInterferenceProfileFailed
bsnAPInterferenceProfileFailed.description: When Interference Profile state changes from PASS to FAIL, notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF. This trap sending can be enable/disable using bsnRrmProfileTrapControlFlag

bsnAPSlotIdTrapVariable.name: bsnAPSlotIdTrapVariable
bsnAPSlotIdTrapVariable.description: Number of Radio Interfaces on the Airespace AP.

bsnAPCoverageProfileFailed.name: bsnAPCoverageProfileFailed
bsnAPCoverageProfileFailed.description: When Coverage Profile state changes from PASS to FAIL, notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF. This trap sending can be enable/disable using bsnRrmProfileTrapControlFlag

bsnAPLoadProfileUpdatedToPass.name: bsnAPLoadProfileUpdatedToPass
bsnAPLoadProfileUpdatedToPass.description: When LOAD Profile state changes from FAIL to PASSt this notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF. This trap sending can be enable/disable using bsnRrmProfileTrapControlFlag

bsnAPNoiseProfileUpdatedToPass.name: bsnAPNoiseProfileUpdatedToPass
bsnAPNoiseProfileUpdatedToPass.description: When Noise Profile state changes from FAIL tp PASS, notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF. This trap sending can be enable/disable using bsnRrmProfileTrapControlFlag

bsnAPInterferenceProfileUpdatedToPass.name: bsnAPInterferenceProfileUpdatedToPass
bsnAPInterferenceProfileUpdatedToPass.description: When Interference Profile state changes from FAIL tp PASS, notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF. This trap sending can be enable /disable using bsnRrmProfileTrapControlFlag

bsnAPCoverageProfileUpdatedToPass.name: bsnAPCoverageProfileUpdatedToPass
bsnAPCoverageProfileUpdatedToPass.description: When Coverage Profile state changes from FAIL tp PASS, notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF. This trap sending can be enable/disable using bsnRrmProfileTrapControlFlag

bsnAPParamUpdateTrapControlMask.name: bsnAPParamUpdateTrapControlMask
bsnAPParamUpdateTrapControlMask.description: Mac Parameters are updated for a Airespace AP interface whenever Dynamic Algorithm are run. This mask describes what update events merit traps to network management. If the bit for a particular event is turned on then notification will be generated on event occurance. Event corresponding bit ----- ----------------- TxPowerChange 1 ChannelChange 2 AntennaChange 4 RTSCTSThresholdChange 8 EDThresholdChange 16 FragmentationThresholdChange 32

bsnAPCurrentTxPowerChanged.name: bsnAPCurrentTxPowerChanged
bsnAPCurrentTxPowerChanged.description: Whenever dynamic algorithms are running and bsnAPIfPhyPowerAutomaticOn is true, Airespace AP Interface's CurrentTxPower might get updated by algorithm. When this occurs notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF along with the currentTxPower for this Airespace AP IF

bsnAPCurrentChannelChanged.name: bsnAPCurrentChannelChanged
bsnAPCurrentChannelChanged.description: Whenever dynamic algorithms are running and bsnAPIfPhyChannelAutomaticOn is true, Airespace AP Interface's CurrentChannel might get updated by algorithm. When this occurs notification will be sent with Dot3 MAC address of Airespace AP and slot ID of Airespace AP IF along with the currentChannel for this Airespace AP IF

bsnRrmDot11aGroupingDone.name: bsnRrmDot11aGroupingDone
bsnRrmDot11aGroupingDone.description: When Grouping is done, this notification will be sent from the previous Group Leader where grouping algorithm was run. It has MAC address of the new Group Leader.

bsnRrmDot11bGroupingDone.name: bsnRrmDot11bGroupingDone
bsnRrmDot11bGroupingDone.description: When Grouping is done, this notification will be sent from the previous Group Leader where grouping algorithm was run. It has MAC address of the new Group Leader.

bsnConfigSaveTrapEnable.name: bsnConfigSaveTrapEnable
bsnConfigSaveTrapEnable.description: If Rogue AP Detection and Removed Traps need to be sent

bsnConfigSaved.name: bsnConfigSaved
bsnConfigSaved.description: When configuration is save either from CLI or web interface This trap will be sent to inform NMS to do refresh

bsnDot11EssCreated.name: bsnDot11EssCreated
bsnDot11EssCreated.description: Whenever a new Ess (WLAN) is created, this notification will be sent along with EssIndex

bsnDot11EssDeleted.name: bsnDot11EssDeleted
bsnDot11EssDeleted.description: Whenever a Ess (WLAN)is deleted, this notification will be sent along with EssIndex

bsnRADIUSServerTrapEnable.name: bsnRADIUSServerTrapEnable
bsnRADIUSServerTrapEnable.description: if RADIUS Server Traps need to be sent

bsnAuthenticationFailureTrapEnable.name: bsnAuthenticationFailureTrapEnable
bsnAuthenticationFailureTrapEnable.description: If Authentication Failure Traps need to be sent

bsn80211SecurityTrapControlMask.name: bsn80211SecurityTrapControlMask
bsn80211SecurityTrapControlMask.description: This mask is for Security related trap controls. Event corresponding bit ----- ----------------- bsnWepKeyDecryptError 1 bsnSignatureAttackDetected 2 By Default all bits are off.

bsnWpsTrapControlEnable.name: bsnWpsTrapControlEnable
bsnWpsTrapControlEnable.description: This control is for WPS(Wireless Intrusion Protection System) related traps.

bsnRADIUSServerNotResponding.name: bsnRADIUSServerNotResponding
bsnRADIUSServerNotResponding.description: This trap is to indicate that no RADIUS server(s) are responding to authentication requests sent by the RADIUS client within the MWAR device(Switch).

bsnAuthenticationFailure.name: bsnAuthenticationFailure
bsnAuthenticationFailure.description: This trap is to inform that client authentication failure has occured at MWAR(Switch). This could be cli/web user, wlan user, or Mac Authorized user. ServiceType will indicate which type of user it is and userName will be cli/web/wlan userName or MacAddress of Mac Authorized User

bsnInitiatorCookie.name: bsnInitiatorCookie
bsnInitiatorCookie.description: The initiator cookie used in an ISAKMP message, to be associated with a trap.

bsnResponderCookie.name: bsnResponderCookie
bsnResponderCookie.description: The responder cookie used in an ISAKMP message, to be associated with a trap.

bsnIpsecTrapsMask.name: bsnIpsecTrapsMask
bsnIpsecTrapsMask.description: This mask describes what events merit traps to network management. If the bit for a particular event is turned on then notification will be generated on event occurance. Event corresponding bit ----- ----------------- bsnIpsecEspAuthFailureTrap 1 bsnIpsecEspReplayFailureTrap 2 bsnIpsecEspPolicyFailureTrap 4 bsnIpsecEspInvalidSpiTrap 8 bsnIpsecOtherPolicyFailureTrap 16 bsnIpsecIkeNegFailure 32 bsnIpsecSuiteNegFailure 64 bsnIpsecInvalidCookieTrap 128

bsnIpsecEspAuthFailureTrap.name: bsnIpsecEspAuthFailureTrap
bsnIpsecEspAuthFailureTrap.description: IPsec packets with invalid hashes were found in an inbound ESP SA. The total number of authentication errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the ipsecSaEspInTable table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

bsnIpsecEspReplayFailureTrap.name: bsnIpsecEspReplayFailureTrap
bsnIpsecEspReplayFailureTrap.description: IPsec packets with invalid sequence numbers were found in an inbound ESP SA. The total number of replay errors accumulated is sent for the specific row of the ipsecSaEspInTable table for the SA; this provides the identity of the SA in which the error occurred. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

bsnIpsecEspInvalidSpiTrap.name: bsnIpsecEspInvalidSpiTrap
bsnIpsecEspInvalidSpiTrap.description: A packet with an unknown SPI was detected from the specified peer with the specified SPI using the specified protocol. The destination address of the received packet is specified by ipsecLocalAddress. The value ifIndex may be 0 if this optional linkage is unsupported. If the object ipsecSecurityProtocol has the value for IPcomp, then the ipsecSPI object is the CPI of the packet. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per peer (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

bsnIpsecIkeNegFailure.name: bsnIpsecIkeNegFailure
bsnIpsecIkeNegFailure.description: An attempt to negotiate a phase 1 IKE SA failed. The notification counts are also sent as part of the trap, along with the current value of the total negotiation error counters for ISAKMP.

bsnIpsecSuiteNegFailure.name: bsnIpsecSuiteNegFailure
bsnIpsecSuiteNegFailure.description: An attempt to negotiate a phase 2 SA suite for the specified selector failed. The current total failure counts are passed as well as the notification type counts for the notify involved in the failure.

bsnIpsecInvalidCookieTrap.name: bsnIpsecInvalidCookieTrap
bsnIpsecInvalidCookieTrap.description: ISAKMP packets with invalid cookies were detected from the specified source, intended for the specified destination. The initiator and responder cookies are also sent with the trap. The current count is sent to allow the trap to accurately relfect dropped and throttled traps. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per peer (within a reasonable time period, rather than sending one trap per packet.

bsnRogueAPTrapEnable.name: bsnRogueAPTrapEnable
bsnRogueAPTrapEnable.description: If Rogue AP Detection and Removed Traps need to be sent

bsnRogueAPDetected.name: bsnRogueAPDetected
bsnRogueAPDetected.description: When a Rogue AP is detected this Trap will be sent out along with APMacAddress on which its detected

bsnRogueAPRemoved.name: bsnRogueAPRemoved
bsnRogueAPRemoved.description: When a Rogue AP that was detected earlier no longer exists this Trap will be sent out along with APMacAddress on which its detected

bsnRogueAPDetectedOnWiredNetwork.name: bsnRogueAPDetectedOnWiredNetwork
bsnRogueAPDetectedOnWiredNetwork.description: When a Rogue is detected on the wired network this trap will be sent out. The same trap with bsnRogueAPOnWiredNetwork set to no will clear the previous trap.

bsnApHasNoRadioCards.name: bsnApHasNoRadioCards
bsnApHasNoRadioCards.description: When an AP has no radio cards present on it, the switch sends this trap.

bsnDuplicateIpAddressReported.name: bsnDuplicateIpAddressReported
bsnDuplicateIpAddressReported.description: This trap is issued when the switch or an AP detects another machine using its IP Address. The first variable has value yes if the duplicate IP is reported by an AP. In that case, the second attribute will carry the AP MAC Address. The third variable is the duplicate IP address in question and the last attribute is the MAC Address of the machine that is found to be using the duplicate IP.

bsnAPContainedAsARogue.name: bsnAPContainedAsARogue
bsnAPContainedAsARogue.description: When our AP detects that it is being contained by another AP, this trap is issued. The clear flag is true if the AP is no longer being contained.

bsnNetworkStateChanged.name: bsnNetworkStateChanged
bsnNetworkStateChanged.description: When the 802.11a or b/g network state is changed this trap is issued.

bsnSignatureAttackDetected.name: bsnSignatureAttackDetected
bsnSignatureAttackDetected.description: This trap is sent out when a signature attack is detected by the switch. The standard and custom signatures are predefined on the switch (see bsnSignatureConfig group). The signatures also defines if its detection should be reported. The trap variables bsnSignatureName and bsnSignatureDescription are retrieved from the detected signature definition. Clear Trap Variable is turned on when the signature attack stops. The signature's quiet time configuration speicifes the time after which the clear trap would be sent. bsnSignatureMacInfo indicates whether the signature is used to track pattern matches for all source MAC addresses together or seperately for individual source MAC addresses. bsnSignatureAttackFrequency will carry the value for a specific MAC address or for all MAC addresses depending on bsnSignatureMacInfo.

bsnAPRadioCardTxFailure.name: bsnAPRadioCardTxFailure
bsnAPRadioCardTxFailure.description: This trap is sent by the switch when a radio card on an AP stops transmitting.

bsnAPRadioCardTxFailureClear.name: bsnAPRadioCardTxFailureClear
bsnAPRadioCardTxFailureClear.description: This trap is sent by the switch when a radio card on an AP starts transmitting again after a prior failure.

bsnAPRadioCardRxFailure.name: bsnAPRadioCardRxFailure
bsnAPRadioCardRxFailure.description: This trap is sent by the switch when a radio card on an AP stops receiving.
